Commentary: Tamim is away on the first ball, although in an unconvincing manner. Kemar Roach speeds in from 'round the wicket and gets a length ball to move back into the southpaw with extra bounce. Tamim tries to defend but it takes the inner half and runs behind square leg. They cross for a run.

OUT! CAUGHT! It's a golden duck for Mahmudul Hasan Joy. Roach switches to over the wicket for the right-hander and hurls across a length ball outside off. It lands and shapes back in a shade, again with some extra bounce. Mahmudul Hasan Joy is on the front foot, he has committed himself to the defensive shot. The ball hurries onto this blade, takes the outside edge and Nkrumah Bonner takes a nice diving catch to his right at gully.
Howout: c Nkrumah Bonner b Kemar Roach

Commentary: Back of a length, outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto stays on the back foot and lets it through to the keeper.
This time Shanto is on his toes and defends this delivery with the angle to the leg side.
In the channel outside off, Shanto hangs back inside the crease and defends it with soft hands to the off side.
Bowls it in the right channel outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto is watchful as he lets it be. A successful start for Kemar Roach.
The natural angle of the pacer beats the bat. Around off, angling away, Tamim Iqbal attempts to block but it whizzes past the outside edge.

'CATCH IT' is the shout... but it falls short. Some moisture on the wicket and the ball is gripping. This one is around off, on a length, Tamim lunges and is early into his defensive shot. He ends up chipping it in the air but it falls in front of the mid on fielder.
Fuller and around off, a confident drive off the front foot by Tamim but he finds the fielder at short cover.
Drifting down the leg side, on a good length, Tamim offers no shot. It brushes his pads and rolls away to the keeper.
And again. This one holds up a bit after landing on a length around middle. Tamim is early into the shot as he works it a shade uppishly towards mid-wicket.

A measured stroke from Iqbal. Too full and around off, Tamim Iqbal drives it straight back and Najmul Hossain Shanto ducks at the other end to allow the ball to go over him. The mid on fielder chases it down and they get a couple of runs.

OUT! BOWLED! Off stump goes for a morning walk! Another Bangla batter bags a duck. Kemar Roach posing trouble with the 'round the wicket angle. He lands it around off, on a length and it skids on with the angle. Najmul Hossain Shanto comes forward to defend but is a bit late in bringing his bat down. The ball finds the gap and goes on to demolish the stumps. The leading wicket-taker in Test cricket at this venue is off to a great start. Roach is on fire!
Howout: b Kemar Roach

Commentary: Back of a length, around middle and off, Mominul gets squared up a bit as he defends it down from the back foot.
Dishes out a length delivery in the channel outside off, Mominul covers the line and shoulders arms.

Roach goes very full and fires it around middle and leg. Mominul attempts to flick but misses. It clips his pads and rolls to the right side of the keeper. Joshua Da Silva dives to stop the ball. It's not cleanly done and the batters think about a run. Eventually, no one crossed.
Fraction short and outside off, Mominul Haque allows it through safely to the keeper.
Close to off and on a good length, Mominul sticks on the back foot and blocks it to the off side.
Right on the money. Lands it on a length around off, Tamim Iqbal strides forward and defends it towards short mid-wicket.
FOUR! Aerial but in the gap. Fuller in length, around middle, Tamim Iqbal flicks it with sweet timing and sends it racing away through mid-wicket for a boundary - first of this Test match.
Sliding down the leg side, on a length, Iqbal attempts to flick but misses. That was not too far away from the edge.
Lands it on a good length, around middle, Tamim closes the face of his bat and helps it towards square leg.

Howwzzatt? Perhaps missing the leg stump as the finger stays down. Jayden Seales serves an inswinger. He pitches it around leg and it nips back in to beat the attempted flick shot of Tamim Iqbal. He is rapped on the pads, they appeal but to no avail.
Around off, a touch full, Tamim presses forward with an angled bat and pushes it wide of the gully fielder. A single to end the over.

FOUR! Tamim will play his shots if it's in his zone. Kemar Roach overpitches outside off, Tamim Iqbal leans into the drive and crunches it in front of square on the off side. Good timing and placement, a boundary results.
On a good length outside off, shaping away, Tamim lets it be.
This one is angled in from around off, Tamim is on the front foot in defense.
FOUR! Easy pickings. A little too straight from Roach, on a length and drifting down the leg side, Tamim clips it behind square leg and picks up his second boundary in the over.
Fires it in, very full and on off, Tamim drives it down to mid off.
Bowls it quite wide outside off, on a length, Tamim strides forward and then offers no shot.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! The poor batting form of Mominul Haque continues. He stepped down from captaincy to focus on his batting but it has not started well for him. Jayden Seales joins the party and Bangladesh are in a big spot of bother. The angle of Jayden does the trick. He serves it around off and on a length. Mominul Haque could have left it but has a feel for it inside the line with zero footwork. It kisses the shoulder of his bat and Jermaine Blackwood takes a sharp catch to his right at second slip.
Howout: c Jermaine Blackwood b Jayden Seales

Commentary: Outswinger to greet the new batter. It's on a good length and close to off, Das pushes at it and misses.
Another outswinger from Jayden. This time though the line is too wide outside off and it's an easy leave for Litton Das.
Angles in a length ball, around middle and leg. Das helps it off his pads to short mid-wicket.
In the channel outside off, on a length and shaping away, Das shoulders arms.
Short and wide outside off, it's left alone by Litton Das. A wicket maiden for West Indies!
Full in length, around off, Tamim gets on the front foot and defends it to the off side.
Roach delivers it full and around middle, Tamim flicks it through mid-wicket and collects three runs. Tamim Iqbal completes 5000 runs in Test cricket!
Roach pitches it up and lands an inswinger outside off. It's a tempter but Litton allows it through to the keeper.
Close to off this time, full and shaping in, Litton defends it near his front pad.
Back of a length, around middle and leg, Litton works it down towards fine leg for a run.
Just outside off, on a length and leaving the batter with the seam movement, Tamim shoulders arms.
Pitches it up and outside off, nipping away, Litton Das makes a patient leave.
This is good bowling. Jayden Seales repeats the last delivery, this time from the off stump line, Litton is forced to offer shot and he blocks it to the off side.
Hurls another length delivery in the region outside off, shaping away, Das allows it through.

Jayden Seales pulls his length back as he bends his back. Around off and there is some steep bounce. Litton Das is on the back foot, trying to deal with it and keeps it out safely from the bottom half of his bat.
A little too straight in line on this occasion, Das leans across and flicks it in the gap at mid-wicket for two runs.
Playing with the patience of the batter. Jayden Seales serves another one in the zone outside off, getting it to move away off the seam, Litton Das lifts his bat skywards and lets it go.
Outswinger outside off, on a length, Tamim covers his stumps and makes a leave.
Not much movement on this delivery, on a length and outside off, Iqbal shoulders arms.
Great lines from Roach. Pitching it on and around off, on a length and getting it to nip away. Tamim Iqbal strides forward and then allows it through.
Close to off, on a length, Tamim is on the front foot as he pushes it with an angled bat to point.

That's loose from Tamim Iqbal. Fuller in length and wide outside off, Iqbal spots the chance for a big booming drive but only manages an inside edge. Luckily for him, he has not dragged it onto the stumps.
Quite wide outside off, shaping further away, Tamim Iqbal has nothing to do with it. Maiden.
FOUR! Not the desired start from Alzarri Joseph. A gentle loosener. Back of a length, around off, Litton Das camps back and punches it through the gap at covers for a boundary.
A touch short again, around off, Das rocks back to pull but mistimes his shot to mid on.
Again the length is slightly short and outside off, Das forces it off his back foot to point. Needs to pitch it further up with the surface offering some movement.
Better this time, on a length and outside off, shaping away, Das leaves. The length is right but he needs to bowl a lot closer to the stumps.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Around off, shaping away from a length, Litton Das has nothing to do with it again.
Seales digs in a short ball around leg, Tamim Iqbal gets hurried on but manages to fend it away past square leg for a single.
Touch short again from Seales, around the body. Das hops and eases it onto the leg side for an easy single.
Goes full this time, but down the leg side. Tamim Iqbal looks to flick it away but misses.
Seales switches to around the wicket now and angles it on the pads, Iqbal works it off his legs towards the fine leg region. The batters get a couple of runs.
Shorter in length, around off. The ball shoots up a bit more than expected but Iqbal does well to keep it down.
This is on a fullish length but angling down the leg side. Tamim Iqbal lets it through to the keeper.
Too close for comfort. A length ball, angled in on off stump and just holding its line. Litton Das makes an assured leave.
Pitches it up this time, a fair bit outside off. Das goes chasing after it as he looks to cover drive but misses the ball.
On a good length, around the fifth stump line. Das doesn't offer a shot at it.
Hard length from Joseph, on off. Das camps back and dabs it down towards the point region.
Joseph keeps it on a slightly shorter length and the ball nips back in a touch from around off. Das shoulders his arms at it.
Short of a length, around off and it's another easy leave for Litton Das. Maiden.
FOUR! Overpitched and punished! Seales floats it outside off and Tamim Iqbal leans into the cover drive and strokes it past the diving Alzarri Joseph to collect a boundary.
Length and angles in close to the off stump. Tamim Iqbal leaves it alone.
Uppish but in the gap! Seales pitches it up around off and Iqbal looks to drive off the front foot. Iqbal punches it uppishly to the left of Alzarri Joseph at mid off and picks up a couple of runs
Drifting onto the pads, Iqbal works it around the corner for a single.

FOUR! Loose shot from Litton Das but he gets away with it. Length ball, landing on the grassy area outside off. Das goes chasing after it and gets a thick outside edge that flies over a jumping Jermaine Blackwood at third slip for a boundary.
Back of a length, on the fifth stump line. Litton Das lets it through to the keeper.
Bowls a length ball on middle, Tamim Iqbal defends it back towards the bowler.
Goes outside off this time and on a good length, Tamim Iqbal looks to defend it but misses.
Touch full this time and on middle, Tamim Iqbal blocks it towards short cover.
Fuller and on middle, Iqbal defends it back towards Alzarri Joseph.
Change of length, goes shorter this time, Tamim Iqbal ducks underneath it.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Tamim Iqbal has got a faint edge on it and has to walk back. Alzarri Joseph speeds in and goes full and down the leg side. Iqbal looks to flick it away but once again it's the right leg that makes it look like he's falling over. The ball goes off the edge and to the right of the keeper. Joshua Da Silva dives across to his right and takes a sharp catch. Iqbal departs cheaply after a decent start and the visitors have to start all over again.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: Full and outside off stump. Shaping away from Litton Das who hangs his bat and gets beaten.
Yorker length, angling into the stumps. Litton Das digs it out to short mid-wicket.
Full and shaping away beautifully. It's bowled slightly wide this time and beats the bat of Litton Das.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Catastrophe! Litton Das follows Tamim Iqbal back to the pavilion and the Windies will have two new batters to bowl at. Kyle Mayers bowls this one on a length and angles it in from outside off. Das strides towards the ball and looks to play it off the front foot. It is the scrambled-seam delivery and the ball just holds its line, unlike the last delivery that swung away. Das gets a feather on it and this time Joshua Da Silva takes a simple catch behind the sticks. The visitors are now five down and Mayers gets a wicket in his very first over.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Kyle Mayers

Commentary: FOUR LEG BYES! Attempts a yorker again but strays in line. Angling down leg and clips Nurul Hasan's pads on the way and goes down to the fine leg boundary.

OUT! LBW! Two wickets in the over for Kyle Mayers and the Windies are all over the opposition! Mayers goes a bit wider of the crease and angles in a big inswinger from well outside off. Nurul Hasan looks to pad it away but the ball does come a long way in. Huge appeal from the bowler and it is given. Hasan looks sheepishly at his skipper and does review it. No spike on UltraEdge as the ball is nowhere near the bat and Ball Tracking shows that it's clipping the off stump. The onfield decision stays. Hasan goes for a duck and Bangladesh looking to bow out in a hurry here.
Howout: lbw b Kyle Mayers

Commentary: Fuller in length and down the leg side, Shakib Al Hasan looks to flick it but misses. It goes off his pads to the keeper.
Goes fuller again, Shakib Al Hasan flicks it towards mid-wicket for a brace.
Outside off this time and on a length, Shakib Al Hasan looks to play it towards covers but the ball hits the upper part of his bat and stays down.
Another one outside off, Shakib Al Hasan defends it solidly.
Sticks to his line bowling it outside off, Shakib Al Hasan guides it towards short cover.
Back of a length this time and outside off, Shakib Al Hasan leaves it alone through and towards the keeper.
Full and outside off stump. Good shape into Mehidy Hasan who defends it back to the bowler.
Full and outside off stump. This one swings outwards and beats Mehidy Hasan past the outside edge.
Full again and bowled wide outside off. Mehidy Hasan fends it awkwardly towards gully.
Kyle Mayers continues bowling full and outside off stump. Mehidy Hasan is not sure which way it's going to move and plays at it tentatively. Beats the outside edge of his bat once again.
Full and wide, Mehidy Hasan pushes at it and gets a thickish edge towards third slip. Doesn't carry.
On a good length this time, angling into Mehidy Hasan who defends it with his gloves as the ball shoots up off the surface. Maiden over by Kyle Mayers.

FOUR! That's mistimed in the air and Shakib Al Hasan has a narrow escape. Alzarri Joseph surprises the batter with a short ball that hurries on from the pitch. Shakib attempts to heave it across the line but it takes the top edge and flies behind mid on. Jayden Seales runs back and attempts to catch but it deflects off his hands and reaches the fence. A good attempt nonetheless. With Bangladesh in dire straits, this shot should be avoided by Shakib.
On middle, Shakib Al Hasan flicks it in front of square leg and immediately calls for two. Easily taken.
On a length and down the middle, Shakib Al Hasan defends it solidly.
On a length and wide outside off, Shakib Al Hasan lofts it over covers and gets a couple of runs.
Fuller, bowled with a bit of extra pace and down the leg side. Shakib looks to flick but misses.
Full and straight this time, this is worked away past square leg for a single.
In the channel outside off, Shakib walks forward for a big shot but it nips away to beat the outside edge.
On a good length outside off stump. Shakib Al Hasan tries to step across on the off side and paddle it fine. Misses the line of the delivery and is hit on his body.
Good-length delivery outside off stump, Shakib Al Hasan mistimes a cut shot towards cover.

SIX! Connects this one really well! Shakib Al Hasan has been looking to go after Kyle Mayers all over and finally gets one off the middle of his bat. Full just outside off stump, Shakib Al Hasan makes room for himself and launches it over the long off boundary for a biggie!
Full and down leg. Shakib Al Hasan misses the sweep and the keeper cannot collect it. Bangladesh get an extra run through a bye.
Inswinger this time on a good length. Mehidy Hasan defends this and gets an inside edge towards mid-wicket.

Chance for a run out, missed. Back of a length delivery, Shakib Al Hasan guides it towards point and calls for a single. The fielder collects it really well and has a shy at the end of the batter but misses. Mehidy Hasan gets a lucky escape.
Fuller in length this time, Mehidy Hasan blocks it away.
On middle this time, Mehidy Hasan guides it to the mid off region.
A touch fuller and angling on the pads, Hasan looks to glance it away but misses. The ball goes off the pads and rolls onto the leg side.
This is on the pads again and Hasan just nudges it towards square leg.
This is full and around off, Hasan punches it straight back past the bowler. The mid off fielder gives chase and keeps it down to a couple.
Slightly full and outside off. Shakib Al Hasan takes a couple of steps forward and lets the ball go as it's angling away from him.
Full and bowled on off stump. Shakib Al Hasan is trying to give the bowler a charge and unsettle him but checks the shot and defends the ball close to his body towards covers.
Full on off. Shakib Al Hasan drives it to mid off for a single.
Length ball bowled outside off, Mehidy Hasan knocks it along the ground towards backward point.
Persists with the line outside off, Kyle Mayers bowls it again on a good length and Mehidy Hasan plays a similar shot to third slip.
Fuller this time and asking Mehidy Hasan to drive from outside off stump. He does not oblige and leaves it alone.
Touch fuller and outside off, Shakib Al Hasan gets on his knees and hits it over cover-point. The ball was in the air for a long time but falls in no man's land. A couple of runs are taken.
Shorter one on off, Shakib Al Hasan tries to play late and run it down to third man but finds third slip.
A low full toss this time, outside off and dipping on the batter. Shakib Al Hasan drives it straight towards the fielder at short cover.

Slightly shorter and outside off, Shakib Al Hasan looks to play at it but the ball hits the upper part of his bat and goes down towards the slip cordon. This was an excellent delivery from Kemar Roach.
Shorter one again, Shakib Al Hasan looks to hit it but misses.
Goes fuller this time and angles it on the pads, Shakib Al Hasan flicks it towards square leg for one.
Back-of-the-hand slower delivery bowled on a yorker length outside off. Shakib Al Hasan swings hard at it but gets undone by the lack of pace as the ball hits the keeper's pads.
Slower delivery once again, full and on off. Shakib Al Hasan knocks it to backward point.
Length ball on middle. Defended back to the bowler.
Short and really wide, Shakib Al Hasan steps back and cuts it to deep point for two runs.
Slower ball flighted into the air. Yorker bowled wide on the off side and beats Shakib Al Hasan who tries to swing across the line and the wicket-keeper. Collected by first slip.
Slower bouncer outside off, Shakib Al Hasan tries to pull it but mistimes it wide of mid-wicket and retains strike for the next over.
Fuller one way wide outside off, Shakib Al Hasan doesn't bother it. Wide called.
On a length and outside off, Shakib Al Hasan waits for the ball and tries to cut. The ball goes towards the fielder at third man off the outside edge. Single taken.
On a good length and on off, Mehidy Hasan defends it away.
On middle this time and fuller in length, Mehidy Hasan eases it back towards Kemar Roach.
Length ball down the leg side, Mehidy Hasan looks to flick it but the ball hits his thigh and rolls in front.
On middle again, Mehidy Hasan defends it solidly.
Fuller one and on off, Mehidy Hasan drives it straight towards the fielder at mid off.
Full on leg stump. Shakib Al Hasan dabs it to short leg.
Pulls his length back slightly and bowls it outside leg. Shakib Al Hasan puts his pad to it and deflects it away.
Full on the stumps. Fended back to the bowler.
On the pads once again and full, Shakib Al Hasan defends it to square leg.
Shakib Al Hasan skips forward, Gudakesh Motie bowls it full and on the pads, it's flicked behind square leg for a single.
Slightly short and turning away from Mehidy Hasan who lets it go. Gudakesh Motie concedes one run in the first over of his Test career and now, it's time for LUNCH on DAY 1.
Starts a new spell by angling away a length ball outside off, Shakib has nothing to do with it. He wants a sighter as of now.
Lands it on a good length, wide outside off, another leave from Shakib.
Back of a length, around off and angling away, Shakib makes one more leave.
Make it four leaves in a row. Shakib has adopted a cautious approach to start.
Goes full and in the line of the stumps, Shakib knocks it down to long on for one.

OUT! Strangled down the leg side! Early success for West Indies in the session yet again and Bangladesh slip further. A pretty innocuous delivery, drifting down the leg side, on a length, Mehidy Hasan tries flicking but it takes a faint tickle from his bat and flies away to the keeper. Joshua Da Silva collects his third catch of the match and Bangladesh's total reads 77 for 7.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Jayden Seales

Commentary: Short ball on off, Shakib pulls it across the line but not in the gap.
Short and it's been pulled to deep square leg. Shakib denies the single.
That's unplayable. Alzarri Joseph bowls from round the wicket and serves a length ball around off. Shakib attempts to play the line but is beaten by the away movement.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it down safely.
Shortish and around middle, Shakib shuffles back a bit but is cramped for room and is forced to defend it down.
FOUR! Short again from Alzarri Joseph, this time it's wide outside off and Shakib latches onto it. He packs a punch and slaps it through backward point.
Bouncer around leg, Mustafizur Rahman leans back and allows it through.
Fuller and outside off, inviting the drive, Mustafizur Rahman stays back and lets it be.
Angling away from the batter, on a length, Mustafizur Rahman is doing as told, not offering his bat.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Mustafizur Rahman doesn't follow the plan and pays the price. Shakib was showing no confidence in him in the previous over, and it appeared the advice was to not flirt with anything not targeted at his body. Mustafizur Rahman follows this for three balls but loses his patience on the fourth ball. Finds a delivery drivable outside off and tries to showcase his talent. But his attempted drive results in an inside edge and Joshua Da Silva accepts yet another catch behind the stumps.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Jayden Seales

Commentary: Back of a length, around off, Hossain pushes inside the line and misses.
Slightly short and outside off, shaping away, Ebadot Hossain has a tame push at it and misses. Expect Shakib Al Hasan to farm strike from hereon.
FOUR! Whacked away! Alzarri Joseph has been pretty ordinary with his length. Bowls it short and wide, Shakib has no qualms in putting it away to the deep point fence.
Shortish and on off, Shakib steps back and dabs it to deep point. Doesn't take the run.
Fuller and on middle, forced down towards long on. No run taken again.
Short and wide outside off, Shakib goes half-heartedly at it, as he attempts to cut. Gets a bottom edge and it doesn't carry to Joshua Da Silva.
FOUR! A touch short and on middle, angling in, Shakib heaves it over backward square leg and fetches a boundary. One ball left in the over for Shakib to retain strike.

FOUR! Shakib decides to go for the boundary and shows no intention to take a single and retain strike. Back of a length, around off, Shakib rocks back and drags it wide of short mid-wicket. 12 from the over, Bangladesh are 7 away from touching 100.
Darts a length ball on off, Ebadot blocks it well.

DROPPED! Nkrumah Bonner got a hand to it but failed to hang on. Jayden Seales delivers it on a length and outside off, Ebadot Hossain hangs his bat out and edges it to gully. Nkrumah Bonner dives across to his left, and attempts to catch it with one hand but it doesn't stick. The ball goes behind and they get a run. Good result for Bangladesh.
Short and on middle, Shakib pulls it to deep square leg and looks for two. He realizes that the fielder has attacked the ball and sends Ebadot Hossain back eventually.
Angling in around off, on a length and shaping away, Ebadot Hossain tries to defend but misses.
Goes short and around leg, Ebadot Hossain fends it away and it goes down to fine leg. They take the single.

Smartly bowled. Jayden Seales senses the movement from the batter and slips a length ball down the leg side. Shakib shuffles across the stumps and then tries to flick. Misses. Ebadot Hossain will be on strike for the start of the next over.
Alzarri Joseph digs it in short, around leg, Ebadot Hossain gets into a tangle as he awkwardly fends at it. It goes wide of the keeper and towards fine leg. They cross and Shakib returns on strike.
Short and on middle, Shakib steps back and cuts it to deep point and denies the single.
Follows the batter down the leg side with a shortish delivery, Shakib turns it on the leg side. The ball rolls in the gap at mid-wicket but again Shakib doesn't run.
Short and on middle, Shakib rides the bounce and pulls it to deep square leg for a run. Two balls to survive for Ebadot Hossain and Shakib has a word with him.
Spears in a very full ball around off, Ebadot Hossain tries to defend but it whistles past the outside edge. After planting a leg gully, this delivery came as a surprise for the batter.

JUST SHORT! Back of a length, around middle, Ebadot Hossain is on his toes as he fends it away uncomfortably. The ball goes uppishly to short leg where Raymon Reifer is standing a shade deep. It falls in front of his outstretched hands.
Too full in length and around off, Shakib squeezes it out through point and denies the single.
Full in length, around middle, Shakib heaves it over mid-wicket and it falls wide of Kemar Roach running across to his left from wide long on. They decide not to run.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR SHAKIB! His 28th in Tests and 9th versus West Indies. It's been a good attacking knock from the skipper. Fuller and outside off, Shakib this time goes through the line and smashes it towards the long off fence. 100 up for Bangladesh!
Short and on middle, pulled to deep square leg for a run. Again two balls to survive for Ebadot.
Poor delivery. Down the leg side, an easy leave for the number 10. Jayden Seales receives a warning for running on the danger area.
Negotiated safely. Ebadot Hossain gets right behind the line of the delivery and offers a dead bat in defense.
Slightly short and on off, Shakib moves back and lofts it over cover-point. No run taken.

OUT! Shakib holes out! Alzarri Joseph angles in a length ball, around off, Shakib Al Hasan winds up for a big heave-ho over mid-wicket but ends up playing it a lot straighter. It flies down to widish long on and Kemar Roach takes the skier safely. End of a handy knock by the skipper. Bangladesh are nine down for just 103.
Howout: c Kemar Roach b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: Digs it in short, around off, Khaled makes a late leave.
A touch short and outside off, Khaled Ahmed removes his bat from the line of the delivery.

OUT! CAUGHT! Fuller this time, around off, Khaled Ahmed brings down a straight bat in defense but it takes a thick outside edge and flies straight into the hands of Nkrumah Bonner at fourth slip. Khaled Ahmed becomes the sixth batter for Bangladesh to bag a duck. The tourists are bundled out for just 103.
Howout: c Nkrumah Bonner b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: Starts well. Lands a full ball around off, a hint of inward shape, Kraigg Brathwaite is half-forward as he defends.
Again it's an excellent delivery. Mustafizur Rahman serves it around middle and leg, getting it to move back in, Kraigg Brathwaite shuffles back and defends it in front of his pads.
This one is angled away from the batter, outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite allows it through to the keeper.
On a good length, around middle, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it from the back foot to the leg side.
Pitches it up and close to off, shaping in a bit, Kraigg Brathwaite is on the front foot as he defends it down.
A touch short on this occasion, around off, Kraigg is on the back foot as he blocks it to the off side.
Sharp delivery first up from Khaled Ahmed. He is operating from 'round the wicket with the wind. Angles it in around off, skidding off the surface, John Campbell defends it from the back foot.
Lands it on a length and outside off, Campbell tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Sharp pace again, full and skidding down the leg side, John attempts to flick but misses.
Fuller in length and outside off, on a driving length, John Campbell allows it through to the keeper.
Back of a length, on off, John covers the line and blocks it to mid on.

Appeal for an lbw! Nothing from the umpire, and no DRS taken either. Fuller and on middle, angling down, John Campbell tries to flick but misses. It goes off his pads to the fielder on the leg side. Missing leg, easily.

Uppish but safe! Movement and extra bounce from around middle, Kraigg Brathwaite tries to defend but it takes the shoulder of his bat and flies to square leg. It falls away from the fielder stationed there.
Around off, on a length, blocked from the back foot.

PUT DOWN! The leg gully fielder was there for this very reason but fails to do the job. Mustafizur Rahman pitches it around middle, on a length and gets it to shape in. Kraigg Brathwaite tries to defend but it takes the inner edge and files quickly to Mominul Haque who fails to hang on to the catch. That's a big miss, we all know Kraigg Brathwaite's appetite for big runs.
Rare bad shot attempted. Full and wide outside off, Kraigg goes chasing after it but fails to connect.
On a good length and outside off, left alone.
Fuller and on middle, flicked to square leg. Three consecutive maidens to start this innings.
In the channel outside off, an easy leave for John Campbell.
Probing delivery. This one is on a length and outside off, John Campbell is forward in defense but gets a soft outside edge. It falls in front of the slip cordon.
Very full and on middle, Campbell flicks it across the line but finds the fielder at mid-wicket.

Huge shout for an lbw, not given. Too high. Back of a length, around off and angling in, John Campbell walks across and tries to pull but misses. He is hit on the thigh pad, they appeal but unsuccessfully.
Short and outside off, John lets it be.
Fuller in length, on off, Campbell flicks but finds the fielder in front of square on the leg side. Make it four maidens in a row.
Bowls it full and around off, Kraigg covers the line and pushes it back to the bowler.
Angles a full ball around off, a hint of swing, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it with soft hands.
Outside off, left alone with ease.
Fullish and close to off, shaping in, Kraigg defends it from the inner half of his blade to mid-wicket.
Good lines, around off and making the batter life. Kraigg defends it back.
Fuller and on off, the batter has just watchfully blocked this out. Five overs done, West Indies are yet to open their account.
Ahmed angles it in around the top of off, Campbell hangs on the back foot and keeps it out around the point region.

John Campbell and West Indies are finally underway! It has taken them 32 balls but the Windies have their first run on the board. This is dug in a bit short and angled at the body. Campbell pulls it past square leg and collects a single.

FOUR LEG BYES! Khaled Ahmed errs in line and gives away a few runs. Very full and angled in on the pads, Kraigg Brathwaite looks to flick but misses. The ball goes off the pads and runs away past the keeper into the fine leg fence.
Length this time, around middle. Brathwaite nudges it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller and bowled with good pace, close to the off pole. Brathwaite makes an assured leave.
Quick single now and Kraigg Brathwaite too is off the mark! Length ball, on middle, Brathwaite plays it with soft hands in front of square on the leg side and scampers through for a run.

Half an appeal from the bowler but probably going down leg. This is served on a length, around middle and leg and the ball shapes back into the right-hander. Brathwaite looks to tuck it away but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Good-length delivery, around the top of off. Brathwaite defends it out onto the leg side.
Just a shade fuller and on off, Brathwaite plays it late and defends it towards short cover.
This is full but angled well across the batter, no need to play at that.
Gets it a bit closer to the off pole now and keeps it full. Brathwaite lets it through to the keeper once again.

Well bowled and well left as well. Mustafizur Rahman just pulls back the length a touch and bowls it really close to the off stump. Brathwaite reads the line of the ball well and makes the leave. Maiden!
Full and around off, shaping away a bit. Easy leave for John Campbell.
Probing line. Khaled Ahmed gets a bit more pace behind this one and angles it in sharply into the off stump. Solidly defended out though by Campbell.
Full and around off, stroked away towards cover-point.
On a nagging length, nipping back in a bit from outside off. Campbell shoulders arms.
On the fifth stump line and quite full, Campbell isn't interested in playing at it.
The maidens keep on coming, still just the one over scored off by West Indies. A length ball, angled in around off. John Campbell pushes it out towards the cover region.
This is on a fuller length and slanted well across the right-hander. Brathwaite leaves it alone.
In the gap! Good-length ball, around the hips. Brathwaite plays at it with soft hands and keeps it down towards the vacant short leg region. Brathwaite picks up a single.
Full, on off and shaping away. John Campbell keeps it out on the off side.

Mustafizur Rahman pulls back the length and tries to attack the pads but spills it down the leg side. Campbell fails to get any bat on it. Also, the Fizz slips while in his stride and is a bit concerned with the landing area.
Short of a length and around off, Campbell looks to cut from too close to the body but edges it back onto the deck.
Length ball, on off. Campbell defends it off the front foot.
Length, around off, Brathwaite pushes at it off the front foot and picks up a single towards cover-point.
In that channel outside off, Campbell lets it through to the keeper.
Pitched up, outside off and this one shapes away a fair bit after passing the batter. John Campbell offers no shot.

Just short! Khaled Ahmed bowls it around the top of off and the ball just nips back in ever so slightly. John Campbell has a poke at it with soft hands but gets an outside edge that lands in front of the man at second slip.
Around off, Campbell leaves it alone this time.
On off, Campbell pats it towards mid on.
Starts with a fuller one on off, Kraigg Brathwaite looks to defend it but gets a thick inside edge. The ball rolls towards the short mid-wicket region.
On a good length and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite shoulders arms at it.
Similar to the last delivery, Kraigg Brathwaite again leaves it through and towards the keeper.
Ebadot Hossain keeps bowling it on a length and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite doesn't bother at it and lets it go towards the keeper.
Good-length delivery wide outside off, Brathwaite lets it go through and towards the keeper.
A brilliant inswinger. Fuller in length following the batter, Brathwaite blocks it out solidly. Oh, it's a no ball. A late call from the umpire and he has recalled the bowler to bowl the final ball.
Back-of-a-length delivery, Brathwaite guides it towards covers and rotates the strike.
Starts off with an in-drifter on middle and leg, Brathwaite nudges it out on the leg side.
Floated up on off stump, Brathwaite defends it off the front foot.
A bit quicker through the air and on off, Brathwaite strides out to defend.
Nicely flighted and angled into middle, Brathwaite watches it well and keeps it out.
Tossed up this time, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to drive it through covers but mistimes it towards silly mid off.
Quicker and flatter, darted into middle. Brathwaite blocks it out. Shakib Al Hasan starts off with a maiden.
Goes 'round the wicket. Bowls it on a length and outside off, John Campbell looks to play at it but gets a bottom edge. The ball bounces back towards the keeper.
On middle this time and on a length, John Campbell defends it back towards the bowler.
Good-length delivery on middle, John Campbell defends it out. The ball bounces back near the stumps and he blocks it with his leg.
Bowls it outside off, John Campbell looks to slap it but misses.
On a length and on middle, Campbell defends it solidly.
Good-length delivery just outside off, Campbell tries to block it but misses. The ball just aired past his blade and goes into the gloves of the keeper.
Uppish but safe! Mehidy Hasan starts off with a speared-in delivery on the pads, Brathwaite flicks it just past short leg and towards square leg.

FOUR! First sign of aggression from Brathwaite and he picks up a boundary, the first of the innings. Darted in on leg stump, Brathwaite gets low and slogs it into the vacant square leg region for a boundary.
Brathwaite looks to use his feet now but Hasan sees him coming. Hasan pulls back the length and angles it into the pads, Brathwaite defends it out.
Flatter delivery, on middle, Brathwaite keeps it out.
Flatter and quicker, on off. Brathwaite backs away and taps it towards the cover region for a quick single. Good running.
Mehidy Hasan switches to around the wicket and floats it up around middle and leg. John Campbell defends it off the front foot.
On a length and on off, Kraigg Brathwaite eases it towards short cover and straight to the fielder.
Bowls it outside off this time, Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone.
Slightly shorter angling into the batter, Kraigg Brathwaite hops a bit and blocks it away.
Good-length delivery outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite looks to play at it but gets an outside edge. The ball rolls towards the slip.
Touch fuller this time, Brathwaite defends it out solidly.
Back of a length and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone towards the keeper. That will be Tea on Day 1.
Tossed up on off, John Campbell eases it to short cover.
Outside off and short, John Campbell cuts it but straight towards the fielder at point.
Tossed up outside off, John Campbell guides it to gully.
On middle and fuller in length, John Campbell lofts it without much timing and just manages to clear mid off. The fielder chases it down and a couple of runs are taken.
Tossed up delivery, John Campbell defends it solidly.
Bowls it outside off this time, Campbell cuts it to the fielder at point. A quick single is taken. This is good running between the wickets.
On a good length outside off, John Campbell raises his arms and lets it go.
Back-of-a-length delivery, John Campbell gets enough width to tap it towards backward point for a single.
On a good length but wide of the off stump. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves this one alone.
Low full toss on the stumps. Kraigg Brathwaite digs it out firmly.
Good-length delivery bowled on off, Kraigg Brathwaite defends this back to the bowler.
Wide delivery on a length. Kraigg Brathwaite lets it go.
Fuller and on off giving it some air, John Campbell guides it towards the fielder at short cover.
Outside off again and fuller in length, John Campbell drives it to long off and takes a single.
Bowls it on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it to the mid-wicket region.
On middle and fuller in length, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it back towards the bowler.
Similar to the last delivery, this is again blocked back towards Mehidy Hasan.
Fuller in length and down the middle stump line, Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it to backward square leg for a brace.
Ebadot Hossain begins with a short delivery bowled wide outside off, John Campbell slashes it to deep point for a brace.
Corrects his length and goes full on off stump, John Campbell knocks it to mid on.
Good-length delivery outside off, driven to cover.
Ebadot Hossain goes short angled into the body. John Campbell ducks under this one.

LBW SHOUT! Ebadot Hossain angles this one into the batter's pads, John Campbell looks to work it leg side but falls over and gets pinged on the pads. Huge appeal, especially from the keeper but the umpire remains unmoved. They think about the review but Shakib opts against it. On replay, we can see that it would have been the umpire's call on hitting the wickets.
Good-length down leg side. Well stopped by Nurul Hasan behind the wicket diving to his right.
Tossed up on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite guides it to mid on and takes a single.
Fuller in length and on leg, John Campbell nudges it towards mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Much fuller with a hint of turn, Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it away.
On middle and fuller in length, Kraigg Brathwaite looks to defend it but gets a thick inside edge as the ball rolls towards square leg.
Touch fuller this time, quicker too, Kraigg Brathwaite goes on his back foot and defends it back towards the bowler.
Tossed up on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite eases it back towards Mehidy Hasan.
Short ball outside off, John Campbell does not offer any shot.
Fuller this time outside the off stump. John Campbell gets his front foot forward and defends it firmly to cover.
On a good length and angling into the batter. Pitches it wide from the off-stump line and is left alone by John Campbell.
NO BALL! Good length from Ebadot Hossain as he pitches this outside off, John Campbell shoulders arms to it. Ebadot Hossain has overstepped and given away an extra run.
On a good length once again but straighter in line with the stumps. John Campbell works it to square leg for a single.
Ebadot Hossain persisting with the outside off stump line on a good length. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves this one alone as well.
On a good length, outside off. Brathwaite pushes it out towards cover-point.
SIX! This was effortless and beautifully timed. Fuller and around middle and leg, John Campbell smokes it over wide long on fence for a maximum.
Fuller and on middle, John Campbell defends it back towards the bowler.
Similar to the last delivery, this is again defended towards the bowler.
FOUR! On a length and outside off, John Campbell gets across, waits for the ball and slaps it past covers for a boundary.
Touch fuller and down the middle, John Campbell leans forward and defends it to cover.
On middle this time, John Campbell tucks it towards mid-wicket for one.
Full and on the pads, Campbell works it towards the mid-wicket region and picks up a single.
Good-length delivery, outside the off-stump channel, left alone by Kraigg Brathwaite.
Persists with the same line, slightly fuller. Kraigg Brathwaite leaves this one alone as well.
Straighter this time on a good length. Kraigg Brathwaite punches it straight past the bowler for a couple of runs down the ground.
On a good length outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite knocks it to short mid off.
Good-length delivery on middle and leg, Kraigg Brathwaite works it to mid on.
Starts with a fuller delivery on off, John Campbell drives it straight towards the fielder at cover.
Fuller again on middle and leg, John Campbell flicks it towards the mid on region.
Outside off this time, John Campbell pushes it towards covers and gets a couple of runs.
On a good length and outside off, John Campbell leaves it through and towards the keeper.
Outside off and fuller in length, John Campbell drives it straight towards the fielder at mid off.
Goes fuller and just outside off, John Campbell looks to play at it but gets beaten past the inside edge as the ball angles in a long way.
Back of a length outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite plays a loose shot, chasing the delivery. It misses the edge of the bat and goes through to the keeper.
Misses out! A rank half-volley and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite punches it to mid off.
Full again on middle and off. Defended straight back.
Full and wide outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite tries to drive hard, stopped at short mid off.
Short and aimed for the body, Kraigg Brathwaite steps away and lets it through.
Slower delivery, bowled full and in line with the stumps, Kraigg Brathwaite puts his bat down and plays it to short mid off.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Strange, strange dismissal but Mustafizur Rahman provides the much-needed breakthrough for Bangladesh. Mustafizur angles it in on a length and into the off stump from outside off. John Campbell puts a big stride forward and looks to defend it out with soft hands. The ball takes the bottom part of the blade and trickles behind to dislodge one of the bails as Campbell tries to keep it out. Campbell cannot believe it. Can this be the stroke of luck Bangladesh need to get going?
Howout: b Mustafizur Rahman

Commentary: Fires it down the middle, Raymon Reifer defends it solidly.
Outside off this time, shaping it in, Raymon Reifer looks to block it but misses as the ball goes towards the keeper.
Length ball and just outside off, Raymon Reifer doesn't bother playing at it and lets it go.
Much fuller and on middle, Raymon Reifer eases it towards the fielder at silly mid on.
Back of a length and down the leg side, Raymon Reifer gets in two minds but ducks down to leave it alone in the end.
Slightly full outside off stump, Kraigg Brathwaite plays it to short mid off.

Appeal for a run out... SAFE! On a good length and around off, Kraigg Brathwaite taps it towards covers and sets off for a quick single. The fielder over there gets in the direct hit at the bowler's end and there's an appeal for a run-out. The fielding side doesn't seem confident though and the third umpire confirms the same. The replay shows that Brathwaite had grounded his bat down in time. Just the single then.
Good-length ball bowled on middle and leg. Raymon Reifer works it towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Smashes it down the ground! Full on off stump, Raymon Reifer takes a stride forward and hits it straight past mid off to get off the mark in style.
Outside off stump on a good length. Raymon Reifer lets this go to the keeper.
Continues to bowl on a good length and around off. Raymon Reifer knocks it to extra cover.
On a good length and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite lets it go towards the keeper.
Fuller and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite looks to drive it but the ball hits the bottom part of his bat. The ball rolls towards the fielder at mid off.
Fuller in length, on middle and leg, Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it towards short fine leg for one.

Oh, this was close. On a length and outside off, Raymon Reifer looks to defend it but gets a thick outside edge. Excellent effort from Litton Das at second slip diving to his right but he can only get his fingertips on it. Maybe, just maybe, had he left it for Najmul Hossain Shanto at first slip, it could have carried. Single taken.
Fuller one on middle and leg, Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it to the left of leg gully. A diving effort from Litton Das once again but it's a bit too far away from him. Single taken.
On a length and on off, Raymon Reifer drives it straight towards the fielder at cover.

FOUR! Great timing on that shot! Full and angling into the pads, Kraigg Brathwaite uses his wrists and splits the gap between mid on and mid-wicket. The timing was so good that the ball kept running away to the boundary away from the chasing fielders.
Good-length on off stump. Solid defense from Kraigg Brathwaite.
Short and wide outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite can't make the most of it and mistimes his cut to point.
Back-of-a-length delivery, outside off, extra bounce off the wicket, Kraigg Brathwaite fends it to square leg.
On off stump once again but bowled back-of-a-length. Kraigg Brathwaite gets on his toes and defends it back to the bowler.
Slower delivery bowled short and in line with the stumps. Kraigg Brathwaite ducks and the ball just loops over him to the wicket-keeper.
Length ball on middle and leg, Raymon Reifer flicks it but straight towards the fielder at leg gully.
On middle and much fuller in length, Raymon Reifer eases it towards point and takes a quick single.
On off and on a good length, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it towards the fielder at mid on.
Good-length delivery outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite looks to play at it but gets a bottom edge. The ball bounces back towards the bowler.
On a length and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite looks to defend it but the ball hits his gloves and rolls towards the fielder at mid-wicket.
Fuller and down on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite drives it straight but the bowler stops it with his leg. Just a single from the over.
Floated full outside off, defended to short mid off.
Full and on middle. Raymon Reifer knocks it to long on for a single.
Looped up, full and outside off. Defended towards short cover.
FOUR! Powered down the ground! Width offered outside off stump, full and slow. Kraigg Brathwaite uses muscle to thump this straight past mid on for a boundary.
Full and on off, defended solidly.
Bowls the same delivery once again and Kraigg Brathwaite repeats the defensive shot as well. Umpires call for refreshments!
On a length and down the middle, Raymon Reifer guides it towards the mid off fielder.
Bowls it on a good length and outside off, Raymon Reifer doesn't bother at it and lets it through.
Back of a length and wide outside off, Raymon Reifer lets it go through nad towards the keeper.
Much fuller this time, Raymon Reifer defends it towards the fielder at point.
Length ball and outside off, left alone by Raymon Reifer.
A maiden from Ebadot Hossain. Outside off this time and fuller in length, Raymon Reifer defends it to the fielder at short covers.
Shakib Al Hasan begins bowling short and wide, Kraigg Brathwaite goes on his back foot and works it to deep backward point for a brace.
Good-length delivery outside off, Defended to short cover.

Shout for a caught behind! Didn't look out to the naked eye and maybe it was just a review taken out of desperation. Shakib Al Hasan flights it up nicely, around off. The ball grips and turns away sharply as Kraigg Brathwaite looks to defend off the front foot. Brathwaite gets beaten past the outside edge. The keeper though seems absolutely certain that there is an outside edge on it and Shakib Al Hasan does take the review for a caught-behind decision. The third umpire checks UltraEdge and confirms there's no spike on it. Brathwaite survives and Bangladesh lose a review as well.
FOUR! Delicately played! Touch short from Shakib Al Hasan outside off stump. Kraigg Brathwaite takes a step back and cuts it past backward point for a boundary in the wide third man region.
Straighter delivery on a good length. Defended back down the pitch.
On a good length outside off, bowled slower in the air by Shakib Al Hasan. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it towards cover-point.
On a good length and outside off, Raymon Reifer lets it go through and towards the keeper.
Outside off again, Raymon Reifer doesn't bother at it.
FOUR! On a length and down the leg side, Raymon Reifer uses the pace of the ball and just gives it a fine tickle. The ball races through the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Touch fuller and on middle, Raymon Reifer eases it back towards the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Almost an unplayable delivery from Ebadot Hossain and Bangladesh have the second breakthrough. Hossain comes from round the wicket, and goes a bit wide of the crease. This is bowled full and angled into the middle stump line, the ball straightens after pitching as well. Raymon Reifer looks to play at it with an angled bat and ends up playing all around it as the outside edge is found. Nurul Hasan takes a sharp catch diving to his left and the salute celebration is out from Ebadot Hossain.
Howout: c Nurul Hasan b Ebadot Hossain

Commentary: Length ball and wide outside off, Nkrumah Bonner lets it go towards the keeper.
Back-of-a-length on middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite steps back and tries to pull it but mistimes it to mid off.

SAFE! Nkrumah Bonner has no idea what he is doing there but he survives. This is flatter and around off, Kraigg Brathwaite taps it towards cover-point and looks for the single but decides against it. Bonner however is already halfway down the track. The fielder over there is just a tad slow in getting rid of the ball as Shakib Al Hasan whips off the bails. The decision does get sent upstairs but the replay shows that Bonner saved himself by putting in the desperate dive.
Full delivery on off, Kraigg Brathwaite defends with a straight bat.
Full on the stumps. Kraigg Brathwaite works it to mid on and rushes for a quick single. The mid-on fielder makes a meal of it and the misfield allows the batters to take two.
Full on off stump, Kraigg Brathwaite happy to defend this one.
Shakib Al Hasan keeping it simple bowling full and stump to stump. Kraigg Brathwaite plays this one safely.
Fuller in length and down the middle, Nkrumah Bonner guides it towards the fielder at point.
Outside off this time and on a good length, Nkrumah Bonner shoulders arms at it.
Touch fuller and on off, Nkrumah Bonner guides it towards the mid off fielder.
On a full length and on middle, Nkrumah Bonner blocks it away.
Bowls it fuller and on middle, Nkrumah Bonner defends it back towards Ebadot Hossain.
FOUR! This was well-timed by Nkrumah Bonner. Fuller and on off, Nkrumah Bonner bends his knees and creams it past covers for a boundary.
On a good length outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite gets a thickish outside edge to backward point.
Full and on the stumps, defended back down the pitch.
Good-length delivery is angled into the pads. Knocks it to mid-wicket.
On a good length angled in once again, Kraigg Brathwaite works it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Flighted delivery, full and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it back to the bowler.
Good-length delivery, angling in and keeping its line. Kraigg Brathwaite is watchful and plays it well.
Bowls it on a good length and down the middle, Nkrumah Bonner defends it solidly.
Length ball on off, Nkrumah Bonner looks to block it but gets an inside edge and the ball rolls towards the left side of the keeper.
Good-length delivery just outside off, Nkrumah Bonner leaves it alone.

Outside off and on a good length, Nkrumah Bonner looks to drive it but misses. A loud appeal for a caught behind but the finger stays down. The replay shows that the ball went past the outside edge, good decision not to review that one. The UltraEdge also backs the decision.
On middle and quicker too, Nkrumah Bonner defends it away.
Fuller in length and on off, Nkrumah Bonner blocks it solidly.
Flighted on off stump. Defended back to the bowler.
Full and flighted once again. This one turns away and Kraigg Brathwaite plays it well.
Full outside off, a firm defense from Kraigg Brathwaite.
Back-of-a-length delivery on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite goes on his back foot and punches it back.
Full once again and on off stump. Kraigg Brathwaite gets low and defends.
Quicker delivery, angled in off a good length. Cramps Kraigg Brathwaite for space as he steps back and plays it staright.
Good-length delivery on off, Nkrumah Bonner eases it towards point.
Outside off again, Nkrumah Bonner guides it to point and rotates the strike.
Goes fuller this time, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it towards the mid off region.
Fuller and down the leg side, Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it to backward square leg for one.
Outside off and on a good length, Nkrumah Bonner shoulders arms at it.
Back of a length and just outside off, Nkrumah Bonner leaves it alone towards the keeper.
Tossed up, full and on off. Kraigg Brathwaite whips it towards mid-wicket and picks up a single.
Nicely bowled! A touch of flight, on a nagging length and outside off. Bonner caresses it towards cover-point.
Floated up, close to the off pole. Bonner blocks it out on the off side.
This one goes on with the arm! Quicker and flatter, sliding into middle and leg. Nkrumah Bonner does well to rock back and defend it out.
Shorter this time, around off. Bonner goes on the back foot but fails to cut it past point.
A tad bit short and on middle, Bonner goes back inside the crease to work it onto the leg side. End of the over from Shakib Al Hasan and he is going off the field, maybe for a breather.
Lands it on a good length, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it to the mid on fielder.
On a good length and on middle, this is again defended towards the mid on region.
On a length and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone towards the keeper.
Touch fuller and on off, Kraigg Brathwaite guides it towards the fielder at mid on.
On off and on a good length, Kraigg Brathwaite eases it towards mid off.
Length ball outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite guides it to cover and gets a quick single.
Flighted delivery, full and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite lunges and defends it watchfully.
Once again it's flighted and outside off, it's defended off the front foot.

Drags his length back and delivers it just outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite moves back and plays late. He guides it behind backward point and picks up three runs. Ebadot Hossain gives the chase and pulls it back. It seems he has hurt himself in the process and is going out for some treatment.
Flatter and on off, defended off the back foot.
Around off, on a fuller length, it's jammed down on the surface.
The line is straighter, the length is fuller, it's clipped with the spin through mid-wicket for a run.

Huge shout for an lbw, the finger stays down. Shakib is off the field, Litton Das is in charge and he gets convinced to take the DRS. Mustafizur Rahman speeds in from 'round the wicket and angles in a full ball around middle. It skids on with the angle as Nkrumah Bonner tries to defend it with a straight bat but misses. The appeal is not entertained and the Ball Tracking shows that it's missing the stumps. Bangladesh lose one more review.
Outside off, on a length, left alone.
Lands it on a length and just outside off, holding its line, Bonner shoulders arms.
A touch short, on middle and drifting down, Nkrumah Bonner turns it on the leg side but finds square leg.
Good areas from the Fizz. Keeps probing around off, fuller in length, Bonner gets behind the line and defends it off the front foot.
Fuller and outside off, it's driven off the front foot but straight to mid off. Another maiden from Mustafizur Rahman.
A bit short and on off, Kraigg moves back and flicks but finds short leg.
Slightly short again, Kraigg goes back and helps it to mid-wicket.
Loopy and full, outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite gets forward and across before defending it down.
Full and floated, around off, it's blocked calmly off the front foot.
Flighted and full, around off, defended safely once more.
Around middle and spinning down, Kraigg moves back and works it off his pads. Finds short fine leg.
Shout for an lbw again, this time a bit muted one. Mustafizur Rahman serves it on a length, around middle and leg, Bonner tries to defend but misses. He is pinged on the pads. Going down, surely.
That's a snorter. Mustafizur Rahman bends his back and digs it in around off. Nkrumah Bonner jumps on the back foot as he pushes inside the line and misses.
Stifled appeal for an lbw, too high and going down as well. This one starts from the middle stump line, on a length, Bonner is beaten while trying to flick and is rapped on the font pad.
Goes very full and lands it around off, Bonner brings his bat down and defends it to mid on.
Dishes a length ball around off, straightening off the seam a touch, Nkrumah Bonner stays back to push inside the line. He edges it past the gully fielder and collects a couple of runs.
Bouncer around leg, Nkrumah Bonner sits underneath it with ease.
Perhaps an arm ball, around middle and leg, Kraigg nudges it behind square leg for a run.
Nicely flighted, it's full and around off, Bonner drives it past the bowler to mid off.
Tossed up and wide outside off, it's left alone.
Fullish and on off, stroked off the front foot to mid off.
Shakib pulls his length back and delivers it outside off, Bonner is on the back foot as he slaps it to sweeper cover for a couple.
Flatter and shorter on off, punched wide of the cover fielder for one. The deficit for West Indies is 9 runs. Can they wipe it off before Stumps?
Sliding down the leg side, on a good length, Bonner eases it towards square leg for a run.
Bumper this time, to keep the batter honest. Around leg and Kraigg Brathwaite allows it through to the keeper.
The Fizz returns to over the wicket. He goes wide of the crease to deliver a length ball around off. It's angling away and Kraigg does well to defend it back.
Down the leg side, on a length, Kraigg Brathwaite has pulled down the shutter and shoulders arms.
Switches back to 'round the wicket and darts in a full ball on off, Kraigg is on the front foot as he blocks it from the inner half of his bat. Last ball of the day coming up now...
Mustafizur Rahman lets out a huge grunt and hurls across a full ball around off, Kraigg Brathwaite presses forward and defends it back solidly. That's Stumps on Day 1.
Nice shape! Ebadot Hossain starts off with a fuller-length delivery from wide of the crease. The ball shapes back in nicely from outside off as Nkrumah Bonner defends it out solidly.
The length is pulled back this time and it is bowled pretty wide outside off, Bonner lets it through to the keeper.
On a driving length but on the fifth stump line, Bonner watches it all the way through and decides not to play at it.
BEATEN! Probing delivery from Ebadot Hossain, length, outside off and shaping back in quite a fair bit. Nkrumah Bonner has to play at it and gets beaten past the outside edge.
On a length again, but a bit outside the line of off stump, Bonner shoulders arms at it.
Maiden to start with! A touch fuller and outside off, easy leave for Nkrumah Bonner.
Mustafizur Rahman starts from around the stumps and angles in a length ball on off stump. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out off the front foot.
Slower in pace and angled into middle, Brathwaite stays in his crease and defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, around off. Brathwaite looks to punch it off the back foot but his feet don't move much and Brathwaite mistimes it back onto the deck.

A hint of extra bounce on this occasion. Fullish delivery, angling in from around off. Brathwaite looks to defend it under his eye line but gets a bit surprised by the bounce. He cops a blow on his gloves.
Mustafizur Rahman looks to attack the pads this time but spills it down the leg side, Brathwaite leaves it alone and the keeper collects it safely.

And again! Length ball, around off, the ball shoots up a bit more than usual but Brathwaite does well to keep it down on the off side. Consecutive maidens to start off the day by the Bangladeshi pacers.
Pitches it up and outside off, Bonner drives it crisply to the left of the cover fielder. He dives and stops the ball, thereby stopping the batters in their tracks.
Zippy delivery. Skidding off the surface from a length outside off, Nkrumah Bonner offers no shot.
This time Ebadot angles in a full ball around off, forcing the batter to play, Bonner brings a straight bat down and pushes it defensively back to the bowler.

A bit of indecision this time. Ebadot Hossain delivers it on a length and outside off, Bonner takes a late call of leaving it. He though fails to withdraw his bat and it goes off the bottom half to the off side.
In the channel outside off, Bonner plays it from the crease and finds the gap at point for one.
Serves it on a good length and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite keeps his weight on the back foot and defends it with an angled bat to cover-point.
Wrong line. This one lands on a length around middle and angles down the leg side. Bonner clips it behind square leg and picks up a single.
Fuller this time, around off and shaping in, Kraigg Brathwaite is forward in defense and it goes off the inner edge to mid-wicket.
Slants in a length ball on off, this time Kraigg is more confident in his stance as he covers the line and blocks it back.
Angling down the leg side, on a length, Brathwaite works it off his pads but finds the mid-wicket fielder.
Solid in defense. Around off, on a length, Kraigg gets half-forward and defends it to the off side.
The Fizz comes from over the wicket for the final delivery. Lands it on a length around leg, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it calmly to the leg side.
Slightly short in length, close to off, Nkrumah Bonner stands tall on the back foot and defends it down on the pitch.
Beautiful delivery. This one lands on a length around off and nips back in sharply. Bonner fails to defend and is hit on the thigh pad. It then deflects behind towards the keeper.
Brought the last delivery in and this time around, Ebadot hurls across a length ball that holds its line outside off. Bonner leaves.
Loose from Nkrumah Bonner, a bit uncharacteristic from him. Short in length and outside off, holding its line, Bonner tries to cut but is beaten by the extra bounce.
Pitches it on a good length and outside off, Nkrumah Bonner presses forward to cover the line and then shoulders arms.

Unplayable! What a delivery! Ebadot dishes out a length delivery close to off, Nkrumah Bonner decides to play the trajectory of the ball but it straightens just a hint to beat the outside edge. Excellent over from Ebadot. The replays, later on, show that there was a spike. No one appealed. Strange.
Khaled begins his fresh spell by spearing a full ball on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite leans across and flicks it on the leg side, finds mid-wicket.
Fuller again, around off, Kraigg uses the angle of the bowler and eases it to the left side of mid on. A single is pinched.
On a length around middle, Bonner brings down a straight blade and defends it off the inner half. It rolls towards mid-wicket and they rotate the strike.
Sliding down the leg side, it's worked with the angle to the leg side.
Shortish and wide outside off, Brathwaite flashes and misses.
Too full and on off, defended back solidly.
100 up! Back of a length, around middle and leg, Bonner nudges it down to fine leg for a run.
Fuller in length and outside off, Brathwaite decides to defend it from the back foot. Not a great choice given that Ebadot has the ability to bring the ball back in.
Full again, outside off, Kraigg is on the front foot this time as he defends it to the off side.
FOUR! First boundary of this morning session and West Indies now move in the lead. Too full in length, around off, Kraigg Brathwaite squeezes it out past backward point for a boundary.
The line goes straighter this time, Brathwaite tucks a length ball through mid-wicket for a couple.
A length ball is sliding down the leg side, Kraigg Brathwaite tries to flick but misses. Stays on 49!
Fuller and on off, defended from the middle of the bat to mid on.
Angling in, from a length around off, once again it's defended off the front foot to mid on.
Pitches it up and around off, Bonner punches it down to mid off.

FOUR! Khaled hurls across a surprise short delivery, around middle, Nkrumah Bonner plays a reactive pull shot and times it well behind square leg. Ebadot Hossain moves across to his left in the deep but fails to cut it off. Should have done better.
Presses forward and pushes a full ball to point. Finds the gap and takes a single.
Goes full around off, Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it safely off the front foot to mid on. West Indies' score read 111 for 2.
There is certainly some zip in this pitch. Ebadot Hossain delivers it on a length and outside off, skidding away, Bonner leaves.

Very good bowling. Ebadot Hossain puts it on a length and close to off, Nkrumah Bonner gets forward and then offers no shot. There is some lateral movement as the ball goes very closely past the off pole.
That is defended solidly off the front foot to cover-point. Bonner eyes a run but is sent back.
A tempter this time, outside off and there to be driven, Bonner has nothing to do with it.
In the channel outside off, it's left easily by Nkrumah Bonner.
On a length, around off and shaping in, Bonner tries to defend but it takes the inner edge and rolls to square leg. They cross.
Wide! Wayward bouncer. Way down the leg side, Bonner lets it be. Good diving take by Nurul Hasan.
Outside off, left alone.
Lands it on a length and around off, Bonner is on the front foot as he blocks it to the off side.
Gets on the front foot and dead-bats a full ball to the cover region.

EDGED BUT SAFE! FOUR! What happened there? Neither the keeper nor the first slip fielder moved. The bowler is upset and rightly so. Back of a length, around off and there is some extra bounce. Nkrumah Bonner is opened up in defense and the outside edge flies through the gap between Nurul Hasan and Najmul Hossain Shanto. Both players looked at each other as the ball went behind and crossed the fence. To be honest, that was Shanto's catch.
Fuller in length and outside off, stroked wide of point for a run.
That is defended solidly off the front foot. End of an eventful over.
Tossed up, outside off, Bonner plays very late and guides it past first slip for a couple of runs.
Flatter and around middle and leg, Bonner goes back and defends it to the off side from the outer part of his blade.
Presses forward to a full ball and defends it to the off side.
Gets on the front foot again and blocks a full ball to covers.
Slightly short and around off, Bonner goes back and plays it to the left of point for one.

FIFTY FOR BRATHWAITE, his 26th in Tests and 4th against Bangladesh. Short again, around off, Kraigg moves back and guides it wide of backward point for one. The 50-run stand also comes up. West Indies lead by 19 runs.
On a good length around off, Kraigg defends it from the back foot.
Extra bounce from a good length around off, Brathwaite takes his bottom hand off the handle as he defends it to point.
Delivers it on a length and around off, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it back from the crease.
Angles in a length ball around middle, Kraigg stays back and quietly tickles it to mid-wicket.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it back to the bowler.
Slightly short in length, around leg, Brathwaite glances it through square leg and is content with a couple of runs.
Fuller and on off, defended back to the bowler.
Flighted and around off, Bonner lunges and defends it with soft hands to the off side.
Flatter arm ball around off, full in length, Bonner defends it ahead of his front pad.
Full and flighted, outside off, it's driven wide of mid off for a couple of runs.
Loopy and full, drifting in around off, Bonner is on the front foot in defense.
Skidding in with the angle, from outside off, Bonner plays late in his attempt to beat first slip but he finds the fielder instead.

FOUR! Gorgeous! Kraigg holds the pose momentarily for the cameras. Fuller in length and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite transfers his weight into the drive and creams it through the gap between mid off and extra cover. Wow!
Lands it on a length around middle, Brathwaite helps it gently to the leg side and pinches a single.
Around off, on a length, it's defended from the back foot.
Short in length and outside off, Bonner slaps it to deep point for a single.
Angling in from a length around off, Kraigg gets back and turns it towards mid-wicket.
Lands it on a length and around off, Brathwaite gets forward and plays late to find the gap at point. Takes a single.
Flighted and full, around off, defended back to the bowler.
Skidding into the batter, from around middle, Kraigg moves back and nudges it behind square leg for a run.
Fuller and around off, blocked towards the bowler.
Floated and on middle, it's defended back once more.
Quicker and flatter, around off, Bonner plays late and it drops in front of first slip.

OUT! TIMBER! At last, Bangladesh have a breakthrough, and their skipper has provided them with that. Shakib Al Hasan fires it in flat, an arm ball around off and skidding in off the surface. Nkrumah Bonner hangs on the back foot, offering an angled bat in defense. But it skids in, clips the inside half of his blade and goes on to disturb the stumps. The 62-run stand has been broken. West Indies lead by 31 runs.
Howout: b Shakib Al Hasan

Commentary: Flighted and full on middle, defended solidly.
Short this time, outside off, Kraigg goes back and cuts it through point for a couple.
Spinning in from around off, Kraigg gets back to work it around but it hits the short leg fielder.
Shortish and on off, Brathwaite gets back and punches it to covers for a run.
FOUR! Jermaine Blackwood is away in style. Floated and full, around off, Jermaine Blackwood strides forward and thumps it through extra cover for a boundary.
Flighted and on off, defended from the front foot to the off side.
Flatter delivery, sliding into the pads. Brathwaite nudges it on the leg side.
This is floated up on the stumps, Brathwaite drives it towards mid on.
On middle and much fuller, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it solidly.
Tossed up on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite guides it to mid on.
Tossed up on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite pushes it to mid on for a quick single.
Tossed up outside off, Jermaine Blackwood drives it straight towards the fielder at mid off.
Flights it and lands it full on middle. It's defended down the pitch.
Fuller this time in line with the stumps. Kraigg Brathwaite is confident in defense.
Full on off stump. Defended towards silly point.
Slightly back of a length, Kraigg Brathwaite steps on his back foot and punches it to mid-wicket.
Full this time on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite steps forward and knocks it back to the bowler.
On a good length and straight. Kraigg Brathwaite stands tall and defends.
Flatter and on middle, Jermaine Blackwood defends it off the back foot to mid on.
Goes fuller this time, Jermaine Blackwood blocks it back towards the bowler.
Outside off this time, Jermaine Blackwood eases it to short cover.
Tossed up delivery, Jermaine Blackwood guides it towards the short mid-wicket fielder.
Slower and giving it some air, Jermaine Blackwood presses forward and blocks it well.
Tossed-up delivery on middle, Jermaine Blackwood defends it back towards Shakib Al Hasan. Maiden!
Full on leg stump. Defended towards mid-wicket.
Slightly short and outside off, Brathwaite steps back and slaps it to backward point.

Close! Mehidy Hasan bowls this full and going down leg stump. Kraigg Brathwaite tries to work this leg side and gets an inside edge that goes towards leg gully. The fielder over there can't quite reach it and the ball goes through his legs. Bangladesh keep letting go of their opportunities. West Indies get two runs instead.
Full and on off, defended firmly.
Straighter this time on a good length. Kraigg Brathwaite defends this towards mid-wicket.
A hint of flight on this occasion, around off. Brathwaite lunges forward and blocks it out.
Tossed-up delivery down the middle, Jermaine Blackwood defends it back towards the bowler.
Similar to the last delivery, this is again defended back towards Shakib Al Hasan.
Outside off this time, Jermaine Blackwood hits it towards short cover and straight to the fielder.
Fuller and on middle, Jermaine Blackwood flicks it towards the mid-wicket region.
Fuller and on the stumps, Jermaine Blackwood flicks it towards backward square leg for one.
On a good length and on middle, quicker too, Kraigg Brathwaite works it towards the short mid-wicket fielder.
On a good length outside off, defended back to the bowler.
Mehidy Hasan maintains an off-stump line, bowls it fuller and Jermaine Blackwood knocks it to covers.
Flatter around off, defended solidly.
Wide down the leg side, Jermaine Blackwood lets this go.
Flighted full on middle, Jermaine Blackwood plays it towards short mid-wicket.
Back-of-a-length delivery and on middle, Jermaine Blackwood goes on his back foot and defends it back down the pitch.
Tossed up outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite cuts it towards the fielder at backward point.
On middle with a hint of turn away from the right-hander, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it away.

FOUR! On middle and much fuller, Kraigg Brathwaite gets down on one knee and slogs it across the line. It beats the diving short mid-wicket fielder and scoots past mid on for a boundary. A bit unlike Kraigg Brathwaite but he took the challenge there.
Tossed up and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it solidly.
On off and much fuller in length, Kraigg Brathwaite defends off his front foot.
A touch shorter and around off, Brathwaite punches it out towards the cover region and picks up a single.
Good-length delivery on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite knocks it towards mid on.
Full outside off, fended back to the bowler.
Mehidy Hasan tries attacking the pads but pitches it around the leg stump. Kraigg Brathwaite stays solid in defense.
On a good length but it's bowled outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite defends once again.
Mehidy Hasan consistent with his line but goes full, Kraigg Brathwaite showing his blocking abilities.
Flighted this time on off, Kraigg Brathwaite plays it straight back to the bowler.
Fuller and on off, Jermaine Blackwood blocks it towards the fielder at mid off.
Similar to the last delivery, this is again defended towards the mid off fielder.
On middle this time, Jermaine Blackwood defends it solidly.
Tossed-up delivery, Jermaine Blackwood blocks it back towards the bowler.

An appeal from behind the stumps for LBW but it is turned down. This is the arm-ball from Shakib Al Hasan, on a shorter length and darted into off stump. Jermaine Blackwood looks to play it off the back foot but is a bit late on it. The keeper thinks it has hit the pad first and appeals vociferously but the finger stays down. The replay shows that it was all bat and no pad.
A maiden from Shakib Al Hasan. This is on middle and fuller, Jermaine Blackwood defends it off his front foot.
Ebadot Hossain starts off with a good-length delivery on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Back of a length this time angled into Jermaine Blackwood who defends it back to the bowler.
Good shape from Ebadot Hossain. He needs to bowl closer to the stumps as this one is wide on a good length and left alone by Jermaine Blackwood.
Closer to the off stump this time and slightly back of a length, played towards mid off.
Full on middle, Jermaine Blackwood knocks it towards mid-wicket and tries for a single that is not there. Sent back by Kraigg Brathwaite.

FOUR! It is just not working for Bangladesh! Ebadot Hossain bowls a lovely outswinger on a full length, tempting Jermaine Blackwood to drive. He obliges but gets a massive edge just wide of second slip. To make matters worse, the ball runs towards wide third man for a boundary! Lead crosses 50.
Bowls it on middle and much fuller in length, Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it away.
This was similar to the last one, Kraigg Brathwaite eases it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it outside off this time, Kraigg Brathwaite drives it towards the fielder at short cover.
