Full-length delivery outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite eases it towards the off side.
On middle this time, Kraigg Brathwaite guides it towards the mid on fielder.
Fifth maiden for Shakib Al Hasan. This is on middle and fuller in length, Kraigg Brathwaite hits it but straight towards the fielder at mid on.
Full and on off, Jermaine Blackwood strokes it confidently to mid off.
Slightly shorter and angled into the batter. Jermaine Blackwood negotiates it well back to the bowler.
Ebadot Hossain is banging it in on middle. Jermaine Blackwood blocks it back down the pitch.
Goes a tad bit fuller and attacks the stumps. Jermaine Blackwood uses soft hands and plays it to mid-wicket.
Straight again, on a good length. Jermaine Blackwood is happy to defend this to mid on.
Back-of-a-length delivery, some extra bounce on offer this time, Jermaine Blackwood gets on his toes and defends it with a straight bat. Back to back maidens!
FOUR! On middle and fuller in length, Kraigg Brathwaite gets on his knees and smashes it over mid-wicket for a boundary. This is surprising from Kraigg Brathwaite with Lunch approaching.
Tossed up around off, this is pushed towards the mid on fielder.
Bowls it outside off this time, Kraigg Brathwaite lets it through to the keeper.
Goes fuller and on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it back towards Shakib Al Hasan.
On off this time, Kraigg Brathwaite hits it but finds the fielder at mid off.
Goes fuller and on middle giving it some air, Kraigg Brathwaite drives it towards the fielder at mid on.
On a good length outside the off pole. Played towards cover-point.
Ebadot Hossain is bowling good line and length here and is making the batter come forward. Pitched up, around off, Jermaine Blackwood knocks it to covers.
Ebadot Hossain persists with the same line and goes a little fuller. Jermaine Blackwood plays this one confidently to cover as well.
Ebadot Hossain goes wider outside off this time, trying to tempt Jermaine Blackwood. He leaves it alone.
Straighter line on a good length. Jermaine Blackwood plays a back foot block.
Slightly shorter this time on off, Jermaine Blackwood nudges it towards cover.
Tossed up around off, Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it but finds the fielder at mid on.
On middle this time, Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it back towards the bowler.
Fuller and on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite pushes it to mid on and straight towards the fielder.
Tossed up on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it solidly.
Bowls it fuller and on middle, Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it back towards Najmul Hossain Shanto.
On middle and fuller in length, Kraigg Brathwaite punches it towards the mid on fielder. That will be Lunch on Day 2.
Shakib Al Hasan flights the first ball, full on leg stump. Jermaine Blackwood defends it back to the bowler.
Full again on leg, Jermaine Blackwood works this to deep square leg for a single.
Shakib Al Hasan bowls a full delivery on off stump. Kraigg Brathwaite defends with a full face of the bat.
Shakib Al Hasan continues bowling full, this time on leg, Kraigg Brathwaite works it to mid-wicket.
Full and on off, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it back to the bowler.
Shakib Al Hasan bowls the exact same ball and Kraigg Brathwaite defends it with ease.
Starts with a slightly shorter one just outside leg, Jermaine Blackwood leaves it through and towards the keeper.
Much better line from Mustafizur Rahman. Bowls it fuller and on off this time, Jermaine Blackwood defends it to short cover.
Goes outside leg again, Jermaine Blackwood leaves it alone towards the keeper.
Fuller in length this time, Jermaine Blackwood drives it towards mid off. The fielder makes a good stop diving to his left. Just a single is taken.
On a good length and down the leg side, Kraigg Brathwaite awkwardly flicks it towards backward square leg and rotates the strike.
Length ball and on middle, Jermaine Blackwood flicks it towards backward square leg for one again.
Ebadot Hossain starts with a short delivery outside off stump, Jermaine Blackwood goes on the back foot and clobbers it to covers. Misfield by the cover fielder allows them to take a single.
Full outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite defends this firmly back to the bowler.
Short once again, giving room to Kraigg Brathwaite to free his hands. He slashes it to deep point for a single.
Full and outside the off pole, Jermaine Blackwood drives elegantly but finds the cover fielder.
Slightly back of a length on off, Jermaine Blackwood shuffles back and defends it towards cover.
Inswinger this time angled in from off stump. Jermaine Blackwood pushes it to mid on for a quick single.
Good-length delivery, shaping away, Jermaine Blackwood guides it towards the fielder at short cover.
Bowls it on middle this time, Jermaine Blackwood flicks it towards square leg.
Length ball, swinging away from the batter, Jermaine Blackwood defends it towards the mid off fielder.
Touch fuller in length from Mustafizur Rahman, Jermaine Blackwood defends it to point.
FOUR! Beautiful shot. Overpitched delivery on the off side, Jermaine Blackwood leans forward and drives it past covers for a boundary.
Bowls it outside off this time, Jermaine Blackwood leaves it alone.
Full and angling into the pads. Kraigg Brathwaite flicks this through mid-wicket for a brace.
Ebadot Hossain tries to compensate for the length and bowls this one short and outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite cuts it to deep point for a single.
Good-length delivery angled into Jermaine Blackwood, who just about manages to get an inside edge onto the pads. Half-hearted appeal from the Bangladesh players.
Misses his line and bowls it down leg stump from a good length. Jermaine Blackwood lets it go.
Full and wide outside off. Jermaine Blackwood places it towards the cover fielder.
Back-of-a-length delivery on middle, Jermaine Blackwood fails to keep it out and it thuds against his thigh pad.
Bowls it on a good length, Kraigg Brathwaite eases it towards the fielder at short cover.
On middle this time and on a length, Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it towards the short mid-wicket fielder.
FOUR! Fuller and wide outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite opens the face of the bat, uses the pace of the ball and cuts it past gully to the third man region for a boundary.
On middle this time, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it back towards Mustafizur Rahman.
On middle and slightly shorter, Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it through mid-wicket and collects three runs. This is really good running between the wickets.
Lands it on a good length and on middle, Jermaine Blackwood flicks it towards the square leg fielder.
Khaled Ahmed starts off by bowling on a good length but gets his line wrong. It is angling down the leg side and Kraigg Brathwaite works it to backward square leg for a single.
Good-length delivery again on off, Jermaine Blackwood defends this back to the bowler.
Fuller length on off stump. Jermaine Blackwood plays at it and inside-edges it to square leg.
Sliding down the leg side. Jermaine Blackwood works it off his hips to square leg for a single.

That pitched on the green patch on the surface! Good length in line with the stumps. Khaled Ahmed gets extra bounce off the wicket and Kraigg Brathwaite does well to keep the ball down off the shoulder of the bat.
Good-length delivery on middle off, Worked towards mid-wicket by Kraigg Brathwaite.
Goes shorter and down the leg side, Jermaine Blackwood ducks underneath it. Wide called.
On a length and on middle, swinging it inside, Jermaine Blackwood guides it to mid on and takes a quick single. The 50-run partnership is up between these two as well.
Back of a length and outside leg, Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone.
This is much fuller and outside off, Kraigg Brathwaite steers it behind point for a brace. He moves to 90 now.
Bowls it on a good length, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it towards the short cover fielder.
On a length and down the middle, Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it but finds the fielder at short mid-wicket.
Bowls it fuller this time and straight at the stumps, Kraigg Brathwaite nudges it towards mid-wicket for one.
Good-length delivery to start off with. This is bowled on off, Kraigg Brathwaite defends this to the bowler.
Fuller in length and angled into the pads, Kraigg Brathwaite uses his wrists and works it square of mid-wicket for two runs.
Pulls his length back, serves it on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite steps back and works it to mid-wicket for a quick single.
Good-length delivery on off. Jermaine Blackwood takes a stride forward and defends firmly.
Angled into the pads from a good length. Jermaine Blackwood takes a single to deep square leg.
Length ball going down leg, Kraigg Brathwaite tries to play at it but misses. Khaled Ahmed feels there is a slight nick but no one else agrees.
Tossed up on off with a hint of turn, Jermaine Blackwood defends it towards the off side.
Bowls it fuller and in the line of the stumps, Jermaine Blackwood eases it back towards Shakib Al Hasan.
Similar to the last delivery, this is again defended towards Shakib Al Hasan.
On middle again and fuller in length, Jermaine Blackwood flicks it straight towards the square leg fielder and takes a quick single.
Bowls it outside off this time, Kraigg Brathwaite defends it towards the mid off fielder.
Fuller one and down the leg side, Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it towards the mid-wicket region.

FOUR! This one has pierced the gap in the deep! A half-tracker from Khaled Ahmed and Jermaine Blackwood has all the time in the world to step back and pull this to backward square leg between the two fielders at the boundary.
Good-length delivery on off. Defended towards mid off.
Back-of-a-length delivery, this time on middle. Jermaine Blackwood gets on top of it and blocks it well.
On a good length and nipping back in. Jermaine Blackwood comes on the front foot and it hits him straight on the gloves.

Close again! Khaled Ahmed goes slightly fuller on leg, Jermaine Blackwood closes the face of his bat trying to work it on the leg side but gets a leading edge that lobs up in the air and lands between cover and point. They cross for a run.

OUT! LBW! Finally, Khaled Ahmed gets the breakthrough for Bangladesh and it is the big fish. This is bowled from a bit wider of the crease and is angled in on a length around middle. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to work it onto the leg side and hops to do so but the ball keeps a shade low and Brathwaite gets pinged on the pads. A huge appeal from the bowler and the dreaded finger is raised. The skipper falls 6 runs short of what would have been another stellar hundred but it's time for some respite for Bangladesh. West Indies now lead by 94 runs.
Howout: lbw b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary: Tossed up on off, Jermaine Blackwood defends it towards the off side.
FOUR! Overpitched delivery outside off, Jermaine Blackwood leans forward and creams it past the cover fielder for a boundary.
Length delivery on middle and leg, Jermaine Blackwood tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Nicely flighted, around off, Jermaine Blackwood drives it towards the man at extra cover.
Length and outside off, Jermaine Blackwood defends it solidly.
FOUR! Touch short in length, outside off, Jermaine Blackwood shuffles across and smashes it past covers for a boundary. West Indies lead by 102 runs.
Khaled Ahmed comes around the wicket and bowls a full delivery way outside off stump. Kyle Mayers leaves it alone.
On a good length, angling into Kyle Mayers. Still wide from the stumps and left alone.
Khaled Ahmed needs to make Kyle Mayers play from the angle but at the moment it is wide and Kyle Mayers is happy to just leave it.
Full this time on off stump. Kyle Mayers digs it out past gully for a couple of runs.
Decides to bowl over the wicket. On a good length angling away from Kyle Mayers. He lets this one go to the keeper as well.
Gets closer to the line of the stumps, on a good length. Kyle Mayers gets an edge but soft hands make the ball roll over to the keeper.
Starts off with a flighted delivery, on a length and on middle. Blackwood nudges it towards square leg.
Drifted onto the pads, Blackwood turns it 'round the corner for a single.
Around the wicket now to the left-hander. This is floated up well outside off and Mayers offers no shot to it.
Slightly flatter and on off, defended off the front foot.
Around off this time, Mayers strides forward and blocks it out.
Fuller this time, angled into middle. Kyle Mayers keeps it out on the off side.
Good-length delivery going down the leg stump. Jermaine Blackwood tries to flick it and misses.
Khaled Ahmed goes slightly back of a length angling into the body. Jermaine Blackwood works it awkwardly to point.
On a good length just outside off, keeps a touch low and Jermaine Blackwood gets an inside edge onto his pads.
On a good length, on leg. This is turned off the hips towards deep square leg for a run.
This is banged in outside off, Mayers leaves it alone to the keeper.
On a good length, at the stumps and there's a bit of an extra bounce on this occasion. Mayers does well to fend it away.
A bit quicker and around off, Blackwood blocks it out.
On middle, flicked towards mid-wicket and Blackwood says no to the risky single.
Nicely bowled! Quicker, and angling in from around off. The ball skids on and Blackwood manages to work it towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up this time, on middle. Blackwood nudges it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller and a bit wider of the off pole, Blackwood strokes it towards cover-point and collects a single.
Mehidy Hasan spears this one into the batter's toes as Kyle Mayers digs it out back towards the bowler.
This is pitched up on off, Blackwood solidly defends it off the front foot.
Short of a good length, on the body. Blackwood works it off his hips behind square on the leg side for one.
Nicely bowled. Fuller and into the channel around off, Kyle Mayers lets it through to the keeper.
Probing line once again from Khaled Ahmed. On a fuller length and pretty close to the off stump, Kyle Mayers makes an assured leave.
This is slanted across the left-hander and no shot is offered by Mayers.

Stifled appeal from the keeper but nothing doing says the umpire. This is full and around off, Kyle Mayers looks for the expansive cover drive but gets beaten past the outside edge. There is a noise but probably the bat hit the ground. The bowler seems confident but they don't opt for the review. The replay confirms that there was no spike as the ball went past the bat.
Flighted, on a good length and around off. The ball bounces a bit extra as it turns into the batter. Blackwood does well to adjust and fend it away.
Quicker and flatter, around off. This is defended off the back foot.

Huge appeal this time but the finger stays down. On a length, around off and turning in quite a fair bit. Jermaine Blackwood strides out to nudge it on the leg side but misses and gets rapped on the pads. After some thinking, Shakib Al Hasan decides not to review it. Oh, no! The replay shows that it would have been curtains for Blackwood had it been reviwed. Another poor decision from Bangladesh and this might cost them a lot.
On a length, at the stumps. This is pushed down to mid on.
Nicely tossed up, around off. Blackwood leans forward to defend.
Shorter in length and turning onto the pads, Blackwood tucks it away fine through short fine leg for a single.
Back of a length, around off. Blackwood hops and keeps it out on the off side.
Full and wide of the off pole, left alone by Blackwood.

Almost! Khaled Ahmed keeps on being aggressive and bowls it short this time, at the body. Jermaine Blackwood looks to pull this one but gets hurried on and gets a bottom edge back onto the deck. The ball almost trickles back onto the stumps but Blackwood manages to get his right boot on the ball in time. Living dangerously here, Blackwood.
Back of a length, around middle. This is worked off the back foot behind square on the leg side for an easy single.
On a length, around the top of off. This is pushed out towards mid on.
Length again, spilled down the leg side as Mayers misses the flick.
Tossed up on middle, Jermaine Blackwood flicks it towards the fielder at short mid-wicket.
Goes fuller and on middle, Jermaine Blackwood defends it back towards the bowler.
Touch fuller on middle and leg, Jermaine Blackwood blocks it towards the vacant short leg region.
Much fuller in length, Jermaine Blackwood drives it towards long on and rotates the strike.
Fuller in length and on middle, Kyle Mayers defends it back towards the bowler.
On a length and just outside off, Kyle Mayers leaves it alone. The ball just aired past the off pole and towards the keeper.
FOUR! Streaky boundary! Ebadot Hossain starts with a short and wide loosener. Jermaine Blackwood slashes at it hard and gets a thick outside edge over the slip cordon for an unconvincing boundary!
Good-length delivery on leg stump. Jermaine Blackwood glances it to fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Punched away with authority! Ebadot Hossain bowls short again and gives Kyle Mayers some room. He leans back on the backfoot and thumps it through covers for a boundary!
Back-of-a-length delivery outside off. There is a bit of an extra bounce but Kyle Mayers does well to fend it away past point and pick up a single.
Length ball wide from off stump. Jermaine Blackwood slashes at it and misses as it goes under his bat towards the keeper.
Loopy full toss on off. Jermaine Blackwood tries to make the most of it but mistimes it to covers.

OUT! LBW! Mehidy Hasan just loves bowling to Kyle Mayers and this is the fourth time that he has dismissed him. This is on a length, around middle and leg and seems to be going on with the angle. Mayers looks to block it off the front foot but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal and the keeper seems certain but the umpire is unmoved. It is reviewed by Shakib and UltraEdge confirms that it is pad first and then the ball hit the bat. Ball Tracking shows that the ball straightened and would have gone on to crash into the leg stump. Brilliant review this time from Bangladesh and they have another wicket in this session.
Howout: lbw b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary: Tossed up delivery on middle, Joshua Da Silva eases it towards the mid on region.
On middle again, Joshua Da Silva defends it solidly.
Fuller one and down the middle, Joshua Da Silva blocks it back towards the bowler.
Bowls it fuller in length, Joshua Da Silva flicks it but finds the fielder at short mid-wicket.
Length delivery angling it into the batter, Joshua Da Silva opens the face of the bat and blocks it away. Wicket-maiden from Mehidy Hasan.
What a beauty from Ebadot Hossain! Bowls on a good length outside off. Gets movement away and extra bounce and beats Jermaine Blackwood all ends up.

Ebadot Hossain is on fire. Brings the line closer this time on a good length and it is unplayable as the ball shapes away beautifully. Bangladesh players are convinced there is an edge but the umpire disagrees. They will not review and that is the right decision.
Good-length delivery on off. Jermaine Blackwood manages to work this to third man for a single.
Good-length delivery on middle this time. Joshua Da Silva defends it back to the bowler.
Full this time wide from off stump. Joshua Da Silva works it to point and gets off the mark.

FOUR! Hammered away and that will be FIFTY for Jermaine Blackwood, his slowest in this format of the game. Length ball, around off, Blackwood hangs back and just crunches this one through wide mid off for a boundary. Ebadot Hossain smiles back at the batter in disbelief as Blackwood raises his bat.
Tossed up down the leg side, Joshua Da Silva flicks it towards the fielder at leg slip.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A sharp catch behind the sticks by Nurul Hasan and Mehidy Hasan is turning it on here for his side. Lovely flight and on a nagging length as well, close to the off stump. Joshua Da Silva looks to defend off the front foot but is beaten in flight and the ball just holds its line as well. The outside edge is found and Nurul Hasan makes no mistake. The finger-wag celebration is out from Mehidy Hasan and Da Silva walks back without troubling the scorers much.
Howout: c Nurul Hasan b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary: Goes fuller and outside off, Alzarri Joseph guides it to point and straight to the fielder.
Fuller in length drifting away from the batter, Alzarri Joseph looks to defend it but misses.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Alzarri Joseph defends it towards the fielder at short leg.
Similar to the last delivery on leg, Alzarri Joseph flicks it towards the fielder at leg gully.
Back-of-a-length delivery, angled into the body. Jermaine Blackwood works it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Ebadot Hossain goes full on off stump. Alzarri Joseph defends this firmly back to the bowler.
Goes outside off and full. Alzarri Joseph is happy to leave it alone.
Good-length delivery on middle-off, Alzarri Joseph looking solid in his defensive approach.
Inswinger outside off, bowled on a good length. Alzarri Joseph decides to leave it last minute.
Ebadot Hossain brings the length back, and continues to bowl on off, Alzarri Joseph stands up tall and defends it well. The umpire takes the bails off and it will be Tea on DAY 2.
Tossed up delivery on middle, Jermaine Blackwood flicks it to the fielder at short mid-wicket.
On middle again, Jermaine Blackwood defends it towards the mid on fielder.
FOUR! Poor delivery this, dragged down on middle. Jermaine Blackwood pulls it hard and thumps it past square leg for a boundary.
Fuller in length and on middle, this is flicked towards the mid-wicket region.

Fuller in length and on middle, Jermaine Blackwood nudges it towards mid-wicket and takes a quick single. A better throw at the keeper's end and Alzarri Joseph would have been struggling to make it in time but it is a well-judged run in the end.
On a shorter length with a hint of turn into the right-hander, Alzarri Joseph blocks it well.
Good-length delivery on off, Jermaine Blackwood gets back and defends it towards mid off.
Full delivery outside off, Jermaine Blackwood leaves it alone.
Even wider this time and full, Jermaine Blackwood watches it pass him and go to the keeper.
Pulls the length back, and bowls it wide, Jermaine Blackwood goes for the expansive cut and is fortunate to not get bat on it. Bangladesh players appeal in unison but there is nothing to it.

Almost chops that one back onto the stumps. Ebadot Hossain bowls it on a good length and angles it in from off stump. Jermaine Blackwood gets an inside edge past the stumps and gets a single to fine leg.
Length ball outside off, Alzarri Joseph does not offer any shot.
Bowls it fuller and on middle, Jermaine Blackwood pushes it towards long on and takes a single.
On off this time, Alzarri Joseph guides it to the short cover fielder.
On middle and fuller in length, Alzarri Joseph flicks it towards the fielder at short mid-wicket.
Similar to the last delivery, this is again flicked towards the fielder at the short mid-wicket region.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Another sharp catch from Nurul Hasan behind the stumps and Mehidy Hasan is in the groove now. This is fuller and a bit quicker, around off. Alzarri Joseph goes on the back foot instead of playing it off the front foot. Joseph looks to play for the turn that isn't there as the ball goes straight on. He gets a thick outside edge straight into the keeper's mitts and his stay at the crease is a short one. West Indies lead by 135 runs with just 3 wickets in hand now.
Howout: c Nurul Hasan b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary: Fuller in length and on off with a hint of turn, Kemar Roach leans forward and defends it away.
Good-length ball outside off. Ebadot Hossain is getting good shape away and Jermaine Blackwood leaves it alone.
Ebadot Hossain attacks the leg stump from a good length. Jermaine Blackwood works it to deep square leg for a single.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! The hard work is finally paying off for the Bangladesh bowlers and West Indies are going down in a hurry here. Ebadot Hossain goes full and outside off, inviting the drive from Kemar Roach who just doesn't have the ability of a top-order batter to not give in to the temptation. Roach gets a thick outside edge that flies to the right of third slip where Litton Das takes a very good catch. Just the two wickets remain now for West Indies and Bangladesh will be looking to clean up the tail soon.
Howout: c Litton Das b Ebadot Hossain

Commentary: Gudakesh Motie gets a back-of-a-length delivery on middle to welcome him to Test cricket. He goes back and defends it well.
Ebadot Hossain continues bowling good length but gets his radar off. This one is bowled wide from leg stump and Gudakesh Motie lets it go.
Bowls it down leg side once again from a good length. Nurul Hasan does well to collect the moving ball by diving to his right.
Fuller in length and down the middle, Jermaine Blackwood flicks it towards the leg side.
On middle and fuller, Jermaine Blackwood hits it straight and hard but finds the fielder at long on. He takes a single.
Tossed up on middle, Gudakesh Motie defends it solidly.
On middle again, Gudakesh Motie eases it back towards the bowler.

FOUR! Gudakesh Motie is off the mark in Test cricket and what a way to do it! Bowls it outside off, Gudakesh Motie opens the face of the bat and cuts it past the backward point for a boundary. The lead grows to 141 now.
Goes fuller and on off, Gudakesh Motie looks to block it but gets a thick outside edge as the ball rolls towards the third man. They collect three runs off it, brilliant running.

FOUR! Thickish outside edge! Ebadot Hossain delivers this wide from off and full, Gudakesh Motie decides to go for the expansive drive over covers but instead gets a thick outside edge that flies past the slip cordon for a boundary. Jermaine Blackwood pats Gudakesh Motie on the back and seems happy with the shot.
Ebadot Hossain gets this closer and on a good length. Gudakesh Motie judges it well and lets it go.
Good-length delivery on middle. Gudakesh Motie blocks this back to the bowler.

FOUR! Wow! This is some exciting batting from Gudakesh Motie and he is getting applause from the vice-captain as well. Pitched up, around off. Motie stands tall and just drives on the up, creaming it through extra cover for yet another boundary. The lead is now over 150 runs and that could be a huge psychological advantage for West Indies.
Full and wide down leg side. Gudakesh Motie leaves it alone.
Length delivery on leg stump, Gudakesh Motie works it towards leg gully and Jermaine Blackwood refuses a single.
Goes fuller and on middle, Jermaine Blackwood flicks it towards the leg side and takes a single.

NOT OUT! Close but not close enough and for now, Gudakesh Motie will keep on batting. Mehidy Hasan slides this one on a length and angles it into middle. Gudakesh Motie looks to defend it off the front foot but seems to have misses it and the ball goes on to crash into the pads. Bangladesh seem certain that it is out and go up in unison but the appeal is turned down. Shakib reviews it but UltraEdge shows that the ball took the inside edge before hitting the pads. Review lost then for Bangladesh.
Outside off with a hint of turn, Gudakesh Motie eases it towards point.
Outside off again from Mehidy Hasan, left alone by Gudakesh Motie.
Bowls it fuller and down the leg side, Gudakesh Motie flicks it towards backward square leg for a brace.
Lands it on off this time, Gudakesh Motie guides it to covers. They had a chance for a single but they decide not to take it.

OUT! TAKEN! A stunner from Mehidy Hasan and Khaled Ahmed strikes with the first ball of his new spell. Ahmed steams in and delivers it halfway down the track, outside off. It is there to be hit and Jermaine Blackwood goes after it. Blackwood tries to force it off the back foot over covers but doesn't quite get his timing right. The ball is hit hard and to the left of short cover where Mehidy Hasan dives to his left and pouches it out of thin air. Blackwood is left stunned but has to walk back after a fine knock. The lead currently stands at 155 runs.
Howout: c Mehidy Hasan b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary: Full and outside off, the natural angle taking it away from Jayden Seales who leaves it alone.
Yorker length outside off stump, Jayden Seales gets bat to it and bumps the ball towards second slip.
Full toss on off, Jayden Seales defends with soft hands towards cover and rushes across for a single.

FOUR! Up and over! Khaled Ahmed gets this full on off and Gudakesh Motie makes room and heaves it over mid off. The ball bounces before the boundary and rolls towards it. The fielder is unable to pull it ball and and concedes a boundary!
Good-length delivery this time on middle and off, Gudakesh Motie taps it towards point and runs across to retain strike.
Bowls fuller and on off, Gudakesh Motie eases it to short covers and takes a quick single.
Outside off this time, Jayden Seales defends it towards the fielder at point.
Goes fuller on middle and leg, Jayden Seales blocks it towards the fielder at short leg.
On off this time, Jayden Seales defends it towards the fielder at silly point.

OUT! LBW! Mehidy Hasan rounds up a sensational outing with his fourth wicket to go along with a stunning catch. Hasan angles this one on a length, around off. Jayden Seales gets down on one knee, looking to sweep it away, but misses and gets rapped on the pads. Huge appeal and the finger is raised almost instantaneously. No harm in reviewing and Seales does just that. UltraEdge shows no bat is involved and Ball Tracking comes up with three reds. West Indies have been bundled out for 265 runs and have a first-innings lead of 162 runs!
Howout: lbw b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary: Starts off with a short ball around off. There's good bounce on offer and Tamim Iqbal does well to hop and keeps it down on the off side.

FOUR! Tamim Iqbal is underway with a boundary! Back of a length and outside off, Iqbal waits on the back foot and slaps it through cover-point. Kraigg Brathwaite gives chase and seems to have just pulled it back in time. The replay though shows that Kraigg Brathwaite was in contact with the ropes as he pulled the ball back in and it will be a boundary.
On a good length, slightly closer to the off stump. This time around Tamim Iqbal punches it off the back foot but can't pierce the gap on the off side.
A tad shorter in length, around off. Tamim Iqbal pushes it out towards cover.

Loose shot from Tamim Iqbal and he is fortunate to not chop it back onto the stumps. Kemar Roach angles this one from outside off, Iqbal has a tentative push at it and gets a bottom edge that doesn't go on to hit the off pole.
A dot to end the first over. Fuller this time and closer to the off stump.Tamim Iqbal plays inside the line of the ball as the ball zips past the outside edge.
A gentle outswinger to begin his spell. It's outside off and easily left by Mahmudul Hasan Joy.
Another outswinger outside off, another easy leave. Seales needs to get closer to the stumps.
On a good length around off, defended down from the back foot.
Perfect line and length to beat the bat. Jayden Seales gets close to off, and delivers an outswinger. Joy has no joy in dealing with it. Tries to play the line but is beaten by the movement.
Mahmudul Hasan Joy is away in this Test match. Back of a length, around off, Joy pushes inside the line and edges it wide of gully. Takes two.
In the region outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy makes a watchful leave.
Tamim is looking to play his shots. Fuller in length, around middle, Iqbal flicks it through mid-wicket for two.
Around off, on a length and angling in, Tamim shows the full face of his bat and punches it down to mid on. The fielder cuts it off and they take a run.
Beautifully bowled. Roach hurls across a length ball, around off and getting it to straighten a hint, Mahmudul Hasan Joy feels for it inside the line and misses.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it on the leg side.

Roach goes wide of the crease and lands it on a length outside off, Joy is in two minds, eventually tries to leave but is late in withdrawing his bat. It takes the bottom edge and rolls away towards the slip cordon.
FOUR! Delightful. Fuller in length and outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy leans forward and plays a crunchy square drive for a boundary.
Drifting down the leg side, Tamim tries to flick but misses. It goes off his pads to the keeper. Tamim got strangled down the leg side in the first innings and needs to be careful.
Around middle, on a length, Tamim works it away from the mid-wicket fielder and takes a single.
Angles it in, on a length and close to off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy shoulders arms.
Similar to the last delivery but the line goes wide outside off, an easy leave for Joy.
Seales gets greedy. Tries to bowl an outswinger from the middle stump line. But this one pitches and goes down with the angle as the batter watches it.
Close to off, on a length, it's defended to covers.
Confusion but no harm is done. Fuller and around middle, Tamim nudges it to mid-wicket and comes out searching for a run. His partner sends him back in time.
Play and a miss! Roach puts it on a fuller length outside off, Tamim aims for a booming drive but is beaten by the away movement.
Better this time from the experienced campaigner. An outswinger outside off, this time Tamim respects the bowler and his delivery. Leaves it alone.

EDGED BUT SAFE! A defensive prod from Tamim this time, he tries to block a length ball which is angled into him. The ball though moves away to take the outside edge. Doesn't carry to John Campbell at second slip.
Fuller and outside off, driven through the line but not in the gap.
Serves it on a length and outside off, Tamim keeps his bat close to his body and lets it be.
A bumper close to off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy ducks.
On a length and outside off, nipping away, Mahmudul Hasan Joy allows it through to the keeper. He is standing ahead of the crease to negate the movement.
Fullish and around off, Joy pushes it through extra cover for a couple of runs.
Seales is showing good discipline. Bowling his outswingers in a nice grouping, just outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy shoulders arms.
Back of a length, outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy crouches and evades it.
Surprises the batter with his inswinger. Around off, on a length, Mahmudul defends it back from the crease.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller in length and outside off, it's driven confidently off the front foot but straight to mid off.
Back of a length, around off, hitting the deck hard, Tamim is on the back foot in defense.
Angles in a length ball around off, Tamim covers the line and blocks it safely.
Around off, on a length and going straight on, Tamim pushes inside the line and misses.
Pitches it up, outside off, Tamim Iqbal tries to drive through the line but mistimes it to mid off.
Overpitched this time from Jayden Seales, on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy pushes it down the ground past the man at mid on and comes back for the third run.
Fullish delivery, in the channel around off and angling away. Tamim Iqbal makes a stylish leave.
Well bowled! On a length, slanted across the off stump. Tamim Iqbal has a nibble at it as he looks to play away from the body but is beaten past the outside edge.
FOUR! Up and over, deliberately played! Short and wide, Tamim Iqbal hops and upper-cuts it over the backward point region to find the fence.
FOUR! A juicy full toss now as Jayden Seales overcompensates for the short ball. Tamim Iqbal flicks it through the vacant mid-wicket region to make it back-to-back boundaries.
Another full toss as Jayden Seales loses his radar a bit. This time Tamim punches it back towards the bowler. A solid start so far from the Bangladeshi openers.
Goes fuller this time and angles it into middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy pushes it out towards mid on.
Solid from Joy! On a fuller length, around off and nipping back in sharply. Joy keeps it out on the off side.
Loose shot this time around from Joy. On a shorter length, outside off and shaping away. Joy looks to play away from the body but gets beaten past the outside edge.
Full and around off, Joy leans forward to block it out.
Full again, on off. Joy defends it firmly towards silly mid on.

A bit of a mix-up but no harm is done. This is full again from Kemar Roach and around off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy strokes it to the right of the man at mid off. Joy looks for the single but Tamim Iqbal isn't even looking at him. Joy just about manages to scamper back in time.
Starts off with a loosener does Alzarri Joseph. This is a half-volley outside off, Tamim Iqbal drives it through the cover region for a couple of runs.
FOUR! Not an ideal start by Alzarri Joseph and Tamim Iqbal punishes him. Another half-volley, this time on the pads and this is flicked away into the mid-wicket fence.
Keeps low! This is banged in short and around off, Tamim Iqbal tries to seat under it but the ball keeps low and just goes over his head.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Joshua Da Silva with an exceptional catch behind the stumps and Tamim Iqbal has to depart. Strong comeback by Alzarri Joseph and he provides the first breakthrough for West Indies. This is bowled on a perfect length, in that channel close to the off stump. Once again, Tamim Iqbal tries to have a nibble at it and the hint of away movement catches the outside edge of Iqbal's willow. The ball flies through to towards first slip but Joshua Da Silva springs to his left and takes a one-handed stunner. Bangladesh trail by 129 runs.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: Around the top of off, Mehidy Hasan backs away a bit and keeps it out towards cover.
Back of a length, around off. This is dabbed down towards backward point.
Kemar Roach bowls this slightly full outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy lets this go through to the keeper.
Inswinger, on a good length, close to the off stump. Mahmudul Hasan Joy plays at it and gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
Swings away from the batter, bowled on a wide line slightly full. Mahmudul Hasan Joy hangs his bat out and gets beaten.
Full and on off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy knocks it towards mid off.
Good-length delivery on middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends on the front foot with a straight bat back to the bowler.
Fuller once again on middle and off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy goes through with the shot but gets a thick edge to point.
Back of a length, down the middle, Mehidy Hasan defends it solidly.
Serves a fuller one down the leg side, Mehidy Hasan flicks it towards deep square leg for a brace.
Bowls it outside off this time, Mehidy Hasan puts his bat at it. The ball rolls towards the fielder at slips.

OUT! CAUGHT! Alzarri Joseph with his second wicket in as many overs and the idea of sending Mehidy Hasan up the order hasn't worked for Bangladesh. This is bowled on a good length and close to the off stump. Joseph does get a bit of an extra bounce due to his height. Mehidy Hasan looks to get on top of the bounce and punch it off the back foot but only manages to get an outside edge. Kyle Mayers at first slip takes a safe catch around his chest and Bangladesh are two down now.
Howout: c Kyle Mayers b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: Fuller in length and on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto leans forward and defends it towards the point fielder.
Outside off this time, Najmul Hossain Shanto guides it towards the off side.
Kyle Mayers starts off with a beauty! Wobble seam outside off stump. Moves away from a good length and beats Mahmudul Hasan Joy with ease.
Another one beats the bat. Kyle Mayers pulls this slightly back and continues bowling with a wobble seam. Mahmudul Hasan Joy hangs his bat out and does not connect.
Good-length delivery angled into leg stump. Mahmudul Hasan Joy works it to square leg for a single.
Kyle Mayers comes around the wicket and bowls on a good-length, this time on off. Najmul Hossain Shanto defends this back down the pitch.
Wide of the off stump, going away from the batter. Najmul Hossain Shanto watches as it passes him and goes through to the keeper.
Full and outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto drives it firmly to mid off.
Touch fuller delivery and on off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy flicks it towards the short mid-wicket fielder.
Back of a length, outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy shoulders arms at it.
Change of length again. Goes fuller and on middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy flicks it towards the mid on fielder.
Length ball but this is wide outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy leaves it alone.
This is outside off again, Mahmudul Hasan Joy leaves it alone towards the keeper.
A maiden from Alzarri Joseph. Back of a length angling it into the batter, Mahmudul Hasan Joy punches it towards the cover fielder.
Continues bowling around the wicket to the left-hander. Outside off stump and full. Left alone by Najmul Hossain Shanto
Full on off stump. Najmul Hossain Shanto knocks it to mid on.
Full and wide from the stumps. Najmul Hossain Shanto taps it to short cover.
Kyle Mayers tries bowling this one fuller outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto connects it well towards the cover region.
Good-length delivery on middle. Knocked towards mid on by Najmul Hossain Shanto.
Kyle Mayers adjusts his line and gets it just outside off, angling into the batter. Najmul Hossain Shanto judges the line well and leaves it alone.
Bowls it on a good length and on middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy blocks it back towards the bowler.
Touch fuller and outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy drives it but finds the fielder at mid off.
Bowls it on a length and on off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy punches it towards short cover.
Goes shorter this time and down the leg side, Mahmudul Hasan Joy ducks underneath it.
Outside off this time and on a length, Mahmudul Hasan Joy leaves it through and towards the keeper.
Another maiden from Alzarri Joseph. Fuller in length and on off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy guides it straight towards the fielder at short cover.
Full and wide, from around the stumps, left alone by Najmul Hossain Shanto.
On a length, closer to the off stump. Well watched and well left by Najmul Hossain Shanto.
Streaky but in the gap. Fuller, on a driving length and angling in from outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto drives it through the cover region and picks up a couple of runs.
Early call for two and they will get it with ease, good running. This is angled into the pads, Najmul Hossain Shanto turns it past square leg this time and races back for the second.
Pitched up, around off, left alone.
Roach goes full and straight now, Najmul Hossain Shanto defends it out solidly.
Bowls it on a good length with some extra bounce, Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it solidly.
Goes outside off this time, Mahmudul Hasan Joy lets it go towards the keeper.

FOUR! This is an excellent and perfectly timed shot from Mahmudul Hasan Joy. Fuller and down the middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy stays firm and drives it straight down the ground. Alzarri Joseph just gets his hand on it but the ball races towards long off for a boundary.
Good-length delivery on off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it towards the mid on region.
Bowls it outside off and slightly shorter in length, Mahmudul Hasan Joy leaves it alone.
On a length angling it into the batter, Mahmudul Hasan Joy guides it to cover and straight towards the fielder.
Effort ball from Kemar Roach but does not make the batter play at it. Full and outside off, left alone with ease.
Goes fuller this time outside off, keeps low and Najmul Hossain Shanto manages to bring his bat down in time to smother it.
Full once again and on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto knocks it to covers.
Good-length delivery pitching outside off and then moving away from the left-handed batter. Najmul Hossain Shanto tries to feel for it and gets beaten.
Full and angling in from outside off stump. Najmul Hossain Shanto strides his front foot forward and defends firmly.
FOUR! No trouble with the leg there! Full once again and straying outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto gets a confident stride forward and caresses it wide of mid off for a wonderful boundary!
Goes shorter and on leg, Mahmudul Hasan Joy ducks underneath it.
This is on a good length and on off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy eases it back towards Alzarri Joseph.
This was similar to the last delivery, Mahmudul Hasan Joy again defends it back towards the bowler.
Touch fuller in length and on middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy drives it through covers for a brace. That brings up the 50 for Bangladesh. They now trail by 112 runs.
Shorter and on middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy lets it go towards the keeper.
Shorter one again around middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy ducks underneath it. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 2.
Right on the button. Kemar Roach begins from 'round the wicket angle and slants a length ball on off, Shanto defends it to the off side.
Play and a miss on the second ball. Roach lands it close to off and takes it away with the seam movement. Shanto feels for it and misses it. The ball dies in front of Joshua Da Silva.

FOUR! Confident shot. Fuller in length and outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto gets on the front foot and smacks it through wide mid off for a boundary. Roach won't mind that shot as well, as he got the batter to drive there.
A bit of indecision shown by the batter. Outside off, Shanto takes a late call of leaving it. He tries to withdraw the bat but it takes the bottom edge and rolls behind to the slip cordon.
Fuller and on off, blocked solidly.
Back of a length, on off, Najmul Hossain Shanto goes on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
Fuller and around off, defended watchfully by Mahmudul Hasan Joy.
Angling in around off, fuller in length, Joy defends it back with a straight bat.
A bit too straight this time, full and on middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy leans across and flicks it through square leg for a couple of runs.
Hurls a length ball in the channel outside off, shaping away, Mahmudul Hasan Joy covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Seales serves it full and on off, it's angling in and there isn't much movement present. Mahmudul Hasan Joy covers the line and blocks.
A gentle delivery. A bit short and outside off, holding its line, Mahmudul has nothing to do with it.
Spears it in, very full and on off, Shanto drives it back to the bowler. Roach jumps to collect the ball but ends up deflecting it to mid off.
Back of a length, just outside off and nipping away, Najmul Hossain Shanto stays on the back foot and keeps his bat close to his body. Leaves it.
Fuller and on off, angling in, Shanto drives it down the ground, from the inner half to mid on.
On a length and close to off, Shanto guards his stumps and makes a leave. There is some late away movement as it leaves the batter.
Darts in a length ball on off, Shanto is solidly behind the line of the delivery in defense.
A touch short and on off, Shanto defends it with the angle of the bowler to the leg side. Maiden, first of this morning.
Fuller in length and around off, it's served from wide of the crease, Joy tries to flick but gets a thick inside edge onto the pads.
Wrong line. Too full and wide down the leg side, the batter attempts to flick but misses.
Good leave. This one is on a length and close to off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy takes his front leg forward to cover his stumps and then makes a leave.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and blocks it safely towards mid on.
Fuller and around off, defended solidly off the front foot.
Too full and around off, Joy tries to drive straight but it takes the inner half and goes to mid-wicket. They cross.
Full and around off, Mahmudul is on the front foot and defends it down safely. Both the Bangla batters are looking solid in defense.
In the zone outside off, on a length and shaping away a bit, Joy pushes inside the line and misses.
On a length and outside off, it's left alone.
Fuller and outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks quite assured in leaving this one. His stance shows that he knows where his off stump is.
Beaten! Kemar Roach gets close to off, angling in on a length and then it nips away, Mahmudul Hasan Joy is beaten as he tries to defend the line.
A touch short and outside off, Joy goes on the back foot and punches it to point.
Angling away from the batter, on a length, Najmul Hossain Shanto lets it be.
Back of a length, on top of off, Najmul Hossain Shanto goes on his toes and strokes it to covers.

FOUR! Spanked! On the up but he nailed it. Width there outside off, Najmul Hossain Shanto latches onto it and smashes it through the line. It's aerial but through the gap between mid off and extra cover.
On a length around off, Shanto hangs on the back foot and defends it down.
Digs it in short, around leg, Shanto goes on his toes and works it with gentle hands behind square leg. One is the call and they get it with ease.
Slightly short again, around middle, Joy works it behind square leg and keeps strike.
Kyle Mayers starts by landing a length ball outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy makes a watchful leave.
Fuller and around off, shaping into the batter, Joy defends it close to his body.
A gentle inswinger, outside off, an easy leave for Mahmudul.
Back of a length, a little too wide outside off, Joy allows it through.
Edgy! Mayers puts it on a length and close to off, nipping away a hint, Joy pushes inside the line and edges it past gully. He gets a single.
Fuller and on off, moving in the air, Shanto defends it towards short cover.
Around off, on a length, Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it from the back foot.
Shortish and on off, allowing the batter time to go on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
Bouncer to mix things up. Jayden Seales is forcing the batter on the back foot. Joy ducks. Now watch out for the full tempter.
Not exactly full, it's on a good length and around off, Joy stays back and offers a dead bat in defense.
A bouncer again, ducked under.
Fraction short and on off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy is on his toes and defends it back.
Outside off, left alone.
Another delivery outside off, Shanto offers no shot.
Back of a length and outside off, once again Shanto lets it be.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SLIPS! So often Kyle Mayers does this. He knows his angles and works the magic with his dibbly-dobblies. Kyle Mayers serves three deliveries in the zone outside off but this time he gets close to off and forces the batter to play the line. Najmul Hossain Shanto doesn't do a lot wrong there but the away movement extracts the outside edge from his defensive bat and John Campbell has a simple catch to take at first slip. There was some extra bounce as well. West Indies have their first breakthrough this morning. They still have a lead of 98 runs.
Howout: c John Campbell b Kyle Mayers

Commentary: Full and around off, defended solidly by Mominul.
Kyle Mayers angles this one in on a fuller length and at the stumps, Mominul Haque pushes it out towards mid on.
Begins his spell with a shortish delivery around off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy is on the back foot as he defends it down.
Back of a length, outside off and shaping in a bit, Mahmudul Hasan Joy allows it through.
This one is served on top of off, short in length again, Mahmudul Hasan Joy is solid in his defense from the back foot.
Alzarri Joseph is getting some extra pace and zip off this surface. Delivers it on a length and outside off, Joy allows it through and this one carries nicely to the keeper.
Needless from Joy, this attempt can only bring sorrow to his team. Short in length and outside off, extra pace and bounce, Mahmudul Hasan Joy stays back and tries to slam it over point but misses.
Uses the angle of the bowler and turns it behind square leg for a run.
This is pitched up on the fourth stump line, Mahmudul Hasan Joy shoulders arms at it.
Length ball, angling in from around off and skidding through. Joy defends it firmly towards mid on.
Lovely shape! Kyle Mayers angles this one in from a bit wider of the crease and makes the ball shape away. Joy tries to play at it but is comprehensively beaten.
Length again, around the top of off. This is defended towards cover.

Leg bye! Half an appeal but sliding well down leg. Mayers goes full this time and tries to attack the pads. Mayers bowls it at the toes as Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks to flick it away. Joy misses the flick and the ball goes off his pads towards backward square leg. A leg bye is taken and a no ball is called for overstepping.
This is on off stump, Haque blocks it out.
Well stopped! This is short and wide, Mominul Haque hangs back and slaps it towards backward point where Gudakesh Motie makes a really good diving stop.
Full delivery angling into the pads. Mahmudul Hasan Joy knocks it to mid on.
Full once again on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy plays it once again towards short mid on.
Adjusts his length and pulls it back, angling into the stumps. Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends solidly.
Shorter delivery outside off stump. Mahmudul Hasan Joy raises his arms and lets it go.
Back-of-a-length delivery on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy gets on his toes and defends it back to the bowler.
Alzarri Joseph goes wide from off stump on a good length, and Mahmudul Hasan Joy is happy to let it go.
Full and outside off, shaping away from the left-hander. No shot is offered by Mominul Haque.
And again. This is leaving the left-hander but is just a bit too wide at the moment from Kyle Mayers to make the batter play at it.
On a length and a bit closer to the off stump, Haque shoulders arms to it.
This is fuller and in that channel around off, yet another leave from Haque.
Mayers pulls back the length a bit and bowls it on off. Mominul Haque hops and keeps it down on the deck.

FOUR! Streaky! Finally, Kyle Mayers gets one to just come in with the angle and it almost produces the wicket. Length ball, around off and nipping back in. Mominul Haque tries to push it out on the off side but gets an inside edge past the leg stump and the ball runs away into the fine leg fence.
Alzarri Joseph starts off with a good-length delivery on off, and Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it to mid on.
Pulls his length back, and bowls outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy works it towards point.
Short once again and wide from off stump, Mahmudul Hasan Joy ducks for good measure.
Full and angling into middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy strokes it with a straight bat back past the bowler. The mid-on fielder gives chase and restricts it to a brace.
Slightly short and outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy does not play a shot.
Alzarri Joseph goes straighter on a good length. Mahmudul Hasan Joy works it to mid-wicket for a single.

NOT OUT! In the channel outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy taps it down to backward point and calls his partner through for a quick run. Raymon Reifer scores a direct hit at the striker's end and they all appeal. The decision is referred but Mominul Haque is safely in.
Good-length delivery angled into the pads. Mominul Haque defends it towards mid-wicket.

OUT! GIVEN LBW! Kyle Mayers' clever variations are doing the job for West Indies. His inswinger lands on a length around off, Mominul Haque tries to flick but his bat gets stuck a bit behind the front pad and he gets pinged in front. The appeal is made, and the umpire thinks for a while before lifting his finger. Mominul Haque has a word with his partner and takes the DRS but the Ball Tracking shows that it's clipping the leg stump. Umpire's call and Bangladesh lose their fourth wicket. The deficit for them is 87 runs.
Howout: lbw b Kyle Mayers

Commentary: Too full in length and outside off, Das reaches out and digs it out to the off side.
Full and angling down leg, Litton Das flicks it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Slightly full outside off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy knocks it to short cover.

Huge appeal for LBW...turned down! Alzarri Joseph serves this one on a length and angles it in from around off. Litton Das shoulders arms at it and gets hit on the back leg. Kraigg Brathwaite goes for the review at the last second. There was no shot offered by Litton Das so the third umpire will go directly to Ball Tracking. It shows that indeed the ball was going over the middle stump and it will stay NOT OUT.
Back of a length, around off. This is punched towards cover.
FOUR! Pulled away! This is banged in short and over middle. Litton Das lays into the shot and pulls it with disdain into the mid-wicket fence.
FOUR! Two in a row! Alzarri Joseph overcompensates with a half-volley outside off, Das creams this one through covers for a boundary.
Around the top of off, Das looks to drive but gets it off the inner half of the bat towards fine leg for a single.
On a good length, around off. This is defended out by Joy.
Kyle Mayers bowls full and angles it into the stumps. Litton Das works it through square leg for a single.
Wide from off stump and slightly short. Mahmudul Hasan Joy slashes it to point.
Slower delivery, full and outside off, Keeps low as Mahmudul Hasan Joy lets it go.
Outside off, on a good length. Mahmudul Hasan Joy punches it past covers for a couple of runs.

FOUR! Wide and Mahmudul Hasan Joy makes the most of it! Kyle Mayers bowls on a good length but errs in line. Mahmudul Hasan Joy gets on his back foot and opens the face of his bat to find the third man boundary!
Kyle Mayers decides to bowl full this time on off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy strokes it to mid off.
Length ball, around off. This is pushed towards the cover region for a run.
Around the top of off, pushed out towards cover.
Short of a good length, this is played off the back foot through covers for a single.
Joseph keeps it a bit short and around off. Das keeps it out off the back foot.
On a hard length, around off. Litton Das hangs back and caresses it towards cover-point.
FOUR! The runs are coming thick and fast now for Bangladesh. Back of a length, outside off, this is played on the up and well-manoeuvred past point for a lovely boundary.
Flighted full on middle, played back to the bowler.
Full and wide spinning away from the off stump. Mahmudul Hasan Joy lets it go.
Full once again, on leg. Worked towards mid-wicket.
Straighter but continues bowling full. It's defended back to the bowler.
Flighted close to the stumps. Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends solidly.
Bowls this one quicker on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy gets forward and defends. Gudakesh Motie starts of with a maiden!
Roach misses his mark first up and serves a high full toss on off. Litton Das is taken aback and ends up punching it towards mid on.
Full and straight, this is flicked past mid-wicket for a run.
Length this time, angling onto the pads. Mahmudul Hasan Joy works it behind square on the leg side for one and the 100 is up for Bangladesh They trail by 62 runs now.

OUT! CAUGHT! A loose shot from Litton Das and Kemar Roach strikes in his first over of a new spell. This is served on a good length outside off and the ball zips off the surface. Das looks to drive away from the body but his feet go nowhere. The ball takes the outside edge and Kyle Mayers takes a sharp catch around his chest at first slip. Just when Bangladesh looked to be on a roll, a wicket goes down. You cannot waft at a wide delivery in the name of positive batting. This is poor from Bangladesh and Litton.
Howout: c Kyle Mayers b Kemar Roach

Commentary: This is angled into off from around the wicket. Shakib Al Hasan solidly keeps it out.

Oooh, a bit of aggression straightaway from the skipper. Kemar Roach goes a bit wider of the off stump and Shakib just looks to clobber it away. Shakib is beaten comprehensively though. Hard to believe this approach.
Flighted on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy cuts it to deep point for a single.
Quicker delivery on a good length, angling down leg side. Missed by Shakib Al Hasan and the keeper and they get an extra run as bye.
Flighted on off stump. Defended solidly.
Full and on off stump. Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it back to the bowler.
Full and angled into middle-leg. Mahmudul Hasan Joy works it towards mid-wicket.

Bye! Nicely floated around off and the ball turns away square. Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks for the expansive drive but is beaten and the keeper misses the ball as well. The batters scamper through for a bye.
Fuller and in the zone around middle, Mahmudul Hasan Joy drives it down to mid on.
Pitches it up and outside off, inviting the drive, Mahmudul Hasan Joy obliges but finds mid off.
Slightly behind a good length, around off, Mahmudul Hasan Joy stays solid in his defense from the back foot.
Angling in, fuller and around off, Joy strokes it down the ground. Finds mid on again.
Lands it on a length and around off, Joy taps it down from the back foot to cover-point.

Beauty! Roach goes wide of the crease and slants in a shortish ball around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy hangs on the back foot like a dead duck as he has a tame push inside the line. The ball though moves away late to beat the outside edge.
Loopy and full, around off, Shakib presses forward and defends.
A touch shorter and flatter around off, Shakib moves back and nudges it in front of square leg for a run.
Flighted and around off, defended off the front foot. Joshua Da Silva quips from behind the stumps - 'Nobody wants to stick around, a lot of pressure here boys, not too many shots being played here!'
Flatter and shorter around off, punched in front of square on the off side for a run.
Full outside off,  turning back in, Shakib Al Hasan tries to hammer this but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Beaten! This one doesn't spin back in much, Shakib plays for the turn off the front foot as it whistles past the outside edge.
The batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Fuller and around off, driven back to the bowler.
On a length and close to off, Joy tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Some inward movement again, Joy once again looks to defend close to his body but inside-edges it onto his pads.
Outside off, on a length and holding its line, Mahmudul Hasan Joy shoulders arms.
Spears it in full, around middle and leg, Mahmudul Hasan Joy clips it to deep square leg for one.
Slower through the air, full and around middle, Joy defends it back.
Fuller and around off, turning away a shade, Joy lunges to defend but it takes the outer edge and rolls to the left of point. They cross.
Loopy and around off, turning in, Shakib tries to flick but only manages to push it back, a shade uppishly. Doesn't carry to the bowler.
Around off, spinning in, the batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Flatter and on off, Shakib stays back to defend and keeps it out off the outer half of his blade.
Floated delivery, full and around off, Shakib jumps down the track and drives it back to the bowler.
Fuller in length, around off and angling in, Joy flicks it through mid-wicket and scampers back for the second run. The deficit is now 53 runs.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Another avoidable shot has been played, and this time by the set batter. Back of a length, outside off and shaping away, Mahmudul Hasan Joy rises on the back foot and throws his bat needlessly at this one. The outside edge gets generated and Joshua Da Silva completes the catch diving across to his right. Things unravelling very quickly for Bangladesh here. They still trail by 53 runs and have only four wickets in the bank.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Kemar Roach

Commentary: The batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Edged but safe. Nurul Hasan chases a length ball outside off and edges it behind. It falls in front of the slip cordon.
Fuller and on off, defended off the front foot.
Close to off, on a length and holding its line, it's a brave leave by Nurul.
Flatter and on off, Shakib goes on the back foot and defends it down.
Short again, turning in from around off, Shakib moves back and cuts it towards point for one.
Slower through the air, full and around off, Nurul pushes it with an angled bat to point.
Presses forward and drives a full ball past the bowler. Alzarri Joseph cuts it off at mid off and they cross for a run.
Advances down the track to a full ball around off and knocks it down towards mid on for a run.
Too full in length, around off, Nurul lunges and defends it back to the bowler.
Full and around off, angling in, Shakib gets forward and defends.
Pitches it up and around off, Shakib pushes it defensively to short cover.
Lands it full and outside off, Shakib leans forward and drives it through cover-point for a run. The deficit drops under 50 now.
On a length and outside off, Nurul punches it from the back foot to covers.
Fuller and on off, it's forced back off the front foot. Roach stops it in his followthrough.
Brilliant delivery. Roach goes wide of the crease and angles it on a length around off. Nurul Hasan takes a big stride forward to cover the stumps and shoulders arms.
Slightly short and around off, Shakib gets back and deflects it behind backward point for a run.
Floated and full, around off, Nurul gets opened up in his stance as he defends it back.
Fuller and around off, it's driven through extra cover for a single. Nurul wants the second run but is sent back.
Fullish and on off, Shakib walks forward and drives it back to the bowler.
Flatter and a touch shorter, around off, Shakib Al Hasan goes on the back foot and blocks it down.
Flights it up and serves it full around off, Shakib Al Hasan leans forward and defends it safely. That will be Lunch on Day 3.
Beats the edge straight away. Late movement for Kemar Roach, from a length around off, Nurul pokes at it and misses.

Confusion over a run. A length ball around off, Nurul pushes it firmly to mid off. Slight fumble there and Hasan looks for a run. Shakib sends him back as the fielder sends a wayward throw towards the keeper.
Once again there is some late away movement. Around off, Nurul pushes and misses inside the line.
Lands it on a length and outside off, staying low, Nurul crouches a bit as he keeps it out to point.
This one is angled in around off, on a fuller length, Nurul looks more assured as he presses forward and defends it to mid on.
Unplayable. Angling in on a length around off, Nurul stays back to defend but is beaten by the late away movement. Could have edged it multiple times in this over but Nurul is lucky.

Shout for an lbw, a huge one but the umpire shakes his head. Mayers delivers an inswinger, around off and on a fuller length. Shakib walks forward and across and tries to flick but misses. He is thudded on the pads and West Indies put an unsuccessful appeal. The hosts take the DRS. The impact is outside 3 meters and Shakib remains not out.
On a length, around off, defended to the off side.

Huge appeal again, for an lbw. The finger stays down. On a length, around off, hitting the seam and going through Shakib's defense. It clips a bit of his pad but it's too high. The replays, later on, show that there was a faint inside edge. No one appealed for a caught behind there, the ball had carried to the keeper. An opportunity missed.
Lands it on a length, around off, that is defended solidly off the front foot.
Fuller and around off, Shakib walks forward and drives but finds mid off.
FOUR! Shot! Too full in length and around off, Shakib skips down the track and crunches his drive past the right side of the mid off fielder for a boundary.
A length ball, angling it in from outside off. Nurul Hasan looks to cover drive but gets it off the inner half of the bat towards mid-wicket. A single is taken.
Roach switches to around the wicket for the left-hander and keeps it outside off. Shakib mistimes it towards mid off.
FOUR! Short and wide, punished! This is short and outside off, Shakib Al Hasan plays the horizontal bat shot and slaps it behind point for a boundary.
This is pitched up around off, this is driven through covers for a couple of runs.
Two more and Bangladesh now trail by 34 runs. Back of a length, around off. Shakib hops and punches it through cover-point for a brace.
Very full and on off, this is firmly driven towards long off for a single.
On a fullish length, around the pads. Shakib tucks it past square leg for one.

This is on a shorter length and outside off. Nurul walks towards the ball and edges it down with soft hands past gully. The fielder from backward point gives chase and keeps it down to a couple of runs.
This is pitched up, around off. Nurul Hasan lets it through to the keeper.
Kyle Mayers goes wider of the crease and outside off, Nurul makes yet another leave.
Length ball, angling into off. Nurul plays it towards the gully region.
Beaten! Mayers goes a bit fuller and on the fifth stump line, Nurul Hasan looks to have a poke at it but the ball zips past the outside edge.
On a fuller length and angling into off, Shakib solidly blocks it out.
Uppish but in the gap. Overpitched, outside off, Shakib Al Hasan drives it uppishly through the vacant cover-point region and rotates the strike.

Lovely shot but it is stopped well. Full and straight, Nurul Hasan drives it straight back past the bowler but Raymon Reifer is quick to get to his left from mid on and make the stop. Nurul wants the single but Shakib sends him back.
This is angled into middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.
Just a bit too straight from Roach at the moment, this is flicked towards mid-wicket.
Around the top of off and jagging back in. Nurul Hasan looks to drive but checks his shot and keeps it out.
This is angled in on a fuller length and into leg stump. Shakib backs away and defends it out.
Top of the off stump line, kept out on the off side.
On a good length, around off. Shakib Al Hasan hangs back and taps it towards cover-point for one.
Keeping a shade low. Angled in from outside off, Nurul gets behind the line to make the block.
Length again, around off. Nurul goes on the back foot to keep it out.
It's the change-up delivery from Kyle Mayers this time. Goes wider of the crease and angles it in full and into middle. Nurul Hasan pushes it out towards covers.
Jayden Seales begins with a good-length delivery wide from off stump and angling away, Shakib Al Hasan leaves it alone.
Jayden Seales bowls the same delivery and Shakib Al Hasan continues to let it go.

FOUR! Huge stride forward and leans into this one! Jayden Seales bowls full outside off. Shakib Al Hasan shows good footwork and thumps it through covers. Some ordinary fielding at the boundary gives Shakib four runs.
Back-of-a-length delivery this time. Shakib Al Hasan hangs back and knocks it to covers.
Wide delivery on a good length. Stays a bit low as Shakib Al Hasan offers no shot.
Good length from Jayden Seales on the off stump, Shakib Al Hasan plays it back to the bowler.
On a length and angling into middle and leg. Nurul keeps it out on the leg side.
Full, shaping into off stump. This is nicely driven towards mid off.
Beaten! On a fuller length and outside off, this one just holds its line. Nurul Hasan plays inside the line of the ball and is beaten past the outside edge.
Goes wider of the crease and angles it in a long way into off stump. Nurul keeps it out.
Nurul Hasan walks down the pitch and converts the length ball into a full ball as he plays it towards cover.
Kyle Mayers just pulls back the length a bit and bowls it outside off. Nurul Hasan goes on the back foot and gets a bottom edge back onto the deck. Maiden!

FOUR! Flowing drive from Shakib Al Hasan! Jayden Seales comes around the wicket and angles the ball in from outside off stump. Shakib Al Hasan strides forward to a full delivery and caresses it through covers for a beautiful boundary!
Good-length delivery outside off, Shakib Al Hasan works it to point for a single.
Jayden Seales bowls this on a good length outside off. The ball nips in and misses the off stump as Nurul Hasan leaves the ball.
Slightly back of a length outside off. Defended towards point.
Better length from Jayden Seales attacking the stumps, Nurul Hasan defends it soundly towards cover.
Inswinger once again on a good length, It is in line with the stumps and Nurul Hasan works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Good-length, over middle. Nurul Hasan works it nicely in front of square on the leg side for a couple of runs. Bangladesh trail by only 16 runs now.
Edged but falls well short. This is around off and skidding through, Nurul Hasan looks to driven but gets an outside edge that lands in front of the man at first slip.

EDGED AND FOUR! Nurul Hasan living dangerously here. Around the top of off, Nurul gets another outside edge that goes off the keeper's pads and over the man at first slip. The ball runs away into the third man fence.
On a good length, outside off. This is played towards cover-point.
Length again, around off, Nurul eases it towards cover.
This is pushed a bit wider of the off stump, Nurul Hasan goes back and across to defend it out.
Good short delivery from Jayden Seales attacking the body of Shakib Al Hasan. He plays it uppishly past the slip cordon for two.
Full and on off stump. Shakib Al Hasan defends it towards covers.
Short again this time and on middle. Shakib Al Hasan spins on his heels and pulls it to deep square leg for a single. No real timing in that shot.
Fuller outside off, Nurul Hasan puts his leg forward and leaves it late. The ball goes close to the stumps on its way to the keeper.
Good-length delivery on off stump, Nurul Hasan defends it well this time.
Jayden Seales bowls short but the ball does not rise much after hitting the pitch. Nurul Hasan gets back and punches it towards the cover fielder.
Starts off with a short ball, on leg stump. Shakib Al Hasan half-pulls it towards deep backward square leg for one.
Length ball, on the fifth stump line. Nurul Hasan taps it towards cover.
On a good length, jagging back in from outside off. Nurul Hasan pushes it out towards the bowler.
short of a length this time and on off. Nurul turns it past square leg and picks up a single.
Easy single on offer. Good length, around off. Shakib Al Hasan hops and dabs it down towards cover-point for a quick single. Bangladesh trail by just 6 runs now.

FOUR! Put away with ease by Nurul Hasan and the fifty partnership is up between these two. This is a half-volley around off, Nurul creams it through extra cover for a boundary. The West Indies is now almost wiped off.
Jayden Seales continues around the wicket to the left-hander. On-a-good-length delivery outside off, Shakib Al Hasan defends it to short cover.

Risky shot from Shakib Al Hasan! Fuller this time outside off, Shakib Al Hasan gives it a charge and swings his arms. Mistimes the ball into the air over cover-point as it lands in no man's land. A single is taken.
Back to bowling good length and outside off, Nurul Hasan defends but gets an inside edge to square leg.
Jayden Seales continues bowling the same delivery. Nurul Hasan gets better contact this time and knocks it to covers.
Jayden Seales bowling good length here and sticking to the offside line, Nurul Hasan leaves this one alone.
FOUR! Hammered away and West Indies will have to bat again! Short of a length and well outside off. Nurul Hasan stands tall and slaps it through the cover region for a boundary.
Starts off with a flatter delivery, outside off. Shakib Al Hasan waits for it and cuts it really late past backward point for a run.
On off, this is pushed towards cover.
On a length, with a hint of flight and around off. Nurul defends it out.
FOUR! Cut away nicely! Short and on off, Nurul Hasan rocks back and thumps it through covers for a boundary.
Floated up on leg stump, Nurul flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Around the off stump, Shakib plays it late and opens the face of the bat to guide it down to third man for one.
Good-length delivery on middle. Shakib Al Hasan knocks it to mid-wicket.
Alzarri Joseph continues bowling on a good length outside off. Shakib Al Hasan knocks it back down the pitch.
Slightly short and outside off stump. Shakib Al Hasan slashes he ball past gully for two runs.
full and straight, this is clipped past square leg for a single.
Around the top of off, this is pushed back towards the bowler.
A length ball, around off. Nurul Hasan taps it towards cover-point.
Flatter and around off, tapped away onto the off side for a quick single.
Tossed up on middle, Nurul blocks it out.
On a length and angled into the pads, this one keeps a shade low but Nurul manages to keep it out.
FOUR! Aerial but a safe shot from Nurul Hasan. Tossed up on middle, Nurul just lifts it high and clears mid on with ease as the ball trickles away into the fence.
On off, kept out.
Quicker and flatter, around off. This is played towards cover.
Alzarri Joseph bangs this in short angled into the batter. Shakib Al Hasan swings his bat and pulls it wide of fine leg for a single.
On a good length pitching on middle. Defends it towards short leg.
FOUR! Well controlled by Nurul Hasan! Short again angled into leg, Nurul Hasan steps away from the stumps and uses the angle to pull it backward of square leg for a boundary!

Trying to be a bit too cheeky there Nurul Hasan. This is on a length and angled into leg stump. Nurul looks to make room and come down the pitch but has to check his drive. The ball goes off the pad and the keeper pouches it. There is a slight appeal for caught behind but the umpire remains unmoved. The replay shows that it was all pad and there was no inside edge on it.
Alzarri Joseph adjust his length and goes a little fuller outside off. Defended towards cover.
Back-of-a-length delivery on leg stump. Nurul Hasan gets on his toes and glances towards fine leg for a single.
On a length and around off, pushed towards cover-point.
Nicely flighted, full and on off. Nurul Hasan strokes it towards short cover.
On off, pushed towards the left of the bowler.
A hint of turn on this occasion. This is looped up around off stump and turns away after pitching. Nurul Hasan watches it well and lets it through to the keeper.
Flatter this time, around off. Nurul punches it out towards cover.
Gudakesh Motie fires it in this time, full and on leg stump. Nurul Hasan jams it out on the leg side.
Alzarri Joseph goes short on middle, Shakib Al Hasan gets a single to deep square leg.
Around the wicket to the right-hander as well. Short and on leg. Nurul Hasan gets up and pulls it to backward square leg for a single.
Alzarri Joseph puts this one wide down leg stump. Continues to bowl short but Shakib Al Hasan does not need to play at it.
Better line this time, Short ball angled into the body. Shakib Al Hasan has to duck under this one.
Alzarri Joseph is getting his bouncers right. Similar delivery attacking the batter. Shakib Al Hasan ducks under this one as well.
Bowls on a good length this time, on off stump, Shakib Al Hasan defends it straight back.
Tossed up, on middle. Nurul Hasan gets a good stride forward and defends it out.
Flighted, around off and turning away. Nurul doesn't play at it.
Flatter and on off, blocked out by Nurul Hasan.
Nicely tossed up, outside off. Nurul Hasan creams it but straight to the man at extra cover.
Around middle, this is wristed away through mid-wicket for a single.
Full and around off, Shakib Al Hasan drives it down to long on for a run.
Digs it in short, around off, Shakib turns inside the crease and pulls it to square leg. Finds the fielder.

Bang on the helmet! Another bouncer from Joseph, well-directed at the batter. Shakib tries to pull but misses. It goes past his gloves, pings him on the helmet and goes straight into the hands of Bonner at short leg. A stifled appeal for a catch but nothing doing. No bat, no gloves, only helmet.
Joseph shows no mercy. Hurls across another bouncer, around middle and leg, Shakib ducks safely.
Shakib is bombarded with bouncers at the moment. He is not taking them on at the moment after taking a blow on the helmet. Safely ducked.
Back of a length, on off, Shakib is on the back foot as he defends it to the leg side.
Fraction short, around middle and leg, Shakib turns and glances it across the line. It goes on one bounce to leg gully. End of a fiery over from Alzarri Joseph!
