Short in length, wide outside off, Nurul goes back and cuts it to deep cover for a run. This now is the highest partnership of this Test match.
Turning down the leg side, it's nudged down to fine leg for a run.
Floated and full, around middle, Hasan leans forward and defends it watchfully.
Quicker and flatter, around off, Nurul defends it from the back foot.
Flighted and full, around middle, Nurul works it in front of square leg for a run.
Skips down the track to a full ball and drives it to deepish mid off for a single. Lead moves to 32. Anything over 100 and West Indies will start to worry.
Starts his spell by landing a length ball around off, Shakib gets on the front foot and pushes it to covers.
Fuller in length and outside off, Shakib drives it to short cover where the fielder dives and deflects it towards mid off. They cross for a run.

Shout for an lbw, the finger has stayed down. Has it pitched outside leg? That's the only question, the rest seems fine in favour of the bowler. West Indies opt for the review. Around leg, on a length and skidding off the surface. Nurul Hasan fails to defend off the back foot and is pinged on the back pad. The UltraEdge finds nothing and the Ball Tracking shows that it has PITCHED OUTSIDE LEG, marginally! Review lost for West Indies, they have none left now.
On a length, around middle, it's defended off the front foot.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.

Another shout for an lbw! Not given. West Indies can't review now. A length ball, around leg, Nurul walks forward and tries to defend but misses. He is again hit on the back pad but the umpire shakes his head. The batter had come too far down the track anyway.
Fuller and around off, Shakib defends it off the front foot.
Walks forward to a full ball around off and defends it back to the bowler.
Quicker around off, steered through point for a single.
Turning away from the batter, on the shorter side, Nurul cuts but finds the point fielder.
Tossed up and outside off, left alone.
Flighted and full, wide outside off, Hasan offers no shot.
A length ball around off, Shakib walks forward and across before tapping it down to covers.
FIFTY FOR SHAKIB! Second in this match for the skipper. Three in a row in Tests. On a good length and outside off, Shakib punches it through covers for a run. Bangladesh lead by 35 runs.
Switches to 'round the wicket and serves a length ball down the leg side. Nurul tries to flick but misses. Joshua Da Silva fumbles but no run is taken.
Fuller in length, around off and skidding off the seam, Nurul fails to defend and is hit on the back pad. A muted appeal for an lbw but it's going down the leg side.
On a length and around off, Nurul walks forward and blocks it down.

FOUR! Slapped away! Short in length and outside off, Nurul Hasan latches onto it and slaps it through point. Good batting. The keeper had come up to the stumps and Nurul used the depth of the crease to create room.
Turning back in from around off, Shakin helps it to square leg and picks up a run.
FOUR! Fine shot! Short in length, around off, Nurul immediately drops his weight on the back leg and powers it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
A low full toss on middle, Hasan knocks it down to mid on and rushes across for a sharp single.
Tossed up, around off, Shakib walks forward and brings his bat and pad together in defense.
Flatter and shorter, around off, Shakib stays back and taps it down to point for a run.
Loopy and full around off, Nurul eases it to the right of mid on and charges forward for a run. This time Shakib sends him back.
Lapse in concentration. Short in length and outside off, Shakib tries to punch it down but it beats the outside edge.
CENTURY STAND! Short in length and wide outside off, Shakib cuts it to deep point for a run. This stand has revived some hope in the Bangladesh camp. Lead is 47.
Fuller in length around off, Nurul walks forward and defends it to mid on.
Angles it in, on a length around off, Nurul takes a step down the track and defends it to the off side.
Short in length, around off, Nurul turns and pulls it down to fine leg for a run. Last ball before Tea coming up...
Back of a length, outside off, Shakib stays on the back foot and punches it to mid off. That will be Tea on Day 3.
Flighted and around off, Nurul is on the back foot as he defends it back to the bowler.
A bit short and close to off, Nurul cuts late but still finds the point fielder.
FIFTY FOR NURUL! A timely knock from the wicketkeeper-batter. Flighted and around leg, Nurul tucks it to square leg for a run.

DROPPED AND FOUR! Full and flighted, outside off, Shakib drives it aerially towards mid off where Roach dives across to his right, stretches his one hand but it doesn't stick and goes behind for a boundary. Could have gone with both hands. The lead crosses 50.
Tossed up, around middle, Shakib tries to flick but misses. It takes his pads and lobs near the vacant short leg region.
Fuller and around middle, defended back off the front foot.
Full and angling in from around off, Nurul defends it off the front foot.
Targets the stumps and delivers it on a length, Nurul blocks it again from the front foot.
Fullish and around middle, Nurul flicks it towards short mid-wicket. It goes on one bounce to the close-in fielder.
On a length, around middle and leg, Nurul covers the angle and defends it down.
Slightly short and on off, Nurul punches it from the back foot to covers.
Nearly a yorker, on middle, Nurul digs it out back towards the bowler. Maiden.
Spinning down the leg side, Shakib tickles it down to fine leg for a run.
Short and wide outside off, cut to point.
Loopy and full, around off, Nurul is forward as he defends it to covers.
Slower through the air, full and around off, it's eased away to long off for a single.
Flatter and around off, defended off the back foot.
Flighted and around middle, Shakib works it wide of square leg for a single.
FOUR! Fuller in length and angling down the leg side, Nurul tries to flick but gets a faint tickle. It races away to fine leg for a boundary.
Lands it on a length, around off, it's pushed from the back foot to cover-point.
Sliding down the leg side, on a length, it's tucked to deep square leg for one.
FOUR! Short in length and wide outside off, Shakib reaches out for it and guides it behind backward point for a boundary.
Around off, on a length, Shakib defends it near his front pad.

SAFE! Fuller in length and outside off, Shakib drives it back off the inner half. The bowler tries to stop but perhaps only gets a fingertip. It goes on to hit the stumps at the other end. Nurul is outside the crease and they appeal. The umpire refers it upstairs and the replays find that there is no touch from the bowler.
Beats the bat! Big lateral movement. On a length and outside off, shaping in, Nurul pushes at it and misses.
A hint of shape again, outside off, Nurul tries to drive but misses.
Wide! Wayward delivery, short and way wide outside off. The batter leaves and it's a late call for a wide by umpire Joel Wilson.

FOUR! Jayden Seales should have done better near the fence. Full and around leg, Nurul Hasan flicks it aerially behind square leg. It races away and beats the sliding effort of the fielder for a boundary.
Back of a length, around off, defended down from the back foot.
Full and swinging in the air, around off, Nurul gets forward and defends it to point.
Lands it on a length, around off, Hasan defends it off his back foot.
Around off, on a length and seaming into the left-hander from 'round the wicket angle, Shakib clips it behind square leg for a run.
Outswinger, on a length and outside off, Nurul pushes inside the line and misses.
Another outswinger outside off, Nurul keeps his bat close to his body and allows it through to the keeper.
Serves it on a length and outside off, curling away off the seam, Nurul again lets it be.
Quite wide outside off, an easy leave. Jayden Seales needs to get closer to the stumps.
Closer this time but not close enough. Fuller and just outside off, nipping away, Nurul tries to defend but doesn't goes chasing for the ball.

OUT! TAKEN! Finally, West Indies have a breakthrough. Straight to Kraigg Brathwaite and Shakib Al Hasan cannot believe it! Kemar Roach comes from around the wicket and serves a length ball around off. The ball moves away a bit and there is some extra zip off the pitch. Shakib goes hard at it and punches it uppishly towards short cover where Brathwaite pouches the ball around his head. A top knock from Shakib comes to an end and Roach is absolutely elated. The 123-run stand is broken and Bangladesh are effectively 70 for 7.
Howout: c Kraigg Brathwaite b Kemar Roach

Commentary: Goes fuller and wider, Ebadot Hossain lets it through to the keeper.
Kemar Roach seems to be in the groove now. This is a bit fuller and angling in a long way from outside off. Hossain makes the leave but the ball goes just past the off stump.
Around the top of off, Ebadot gets behind the line of the ball to make the block.
Length again, a bit wider of the off stump. Ebadot Hossain leaves it alone.

Kemar Roach looks for the dream ball as he tries to swing it away from middle and leg stump but the ball just goes on with the angle and down leg. Ebadot Hossain looks to tickle it away but misses. A wicket-maiden then for Kemar Roach!
On a length, outside off and shaping away from the right-hander. Nurul Hasan plays inside the line of the ball.
And again! Angling it in from outside off but the ball shapes away. Just a bit too wide to induce the outside edge.
thrice in a row now from Jayden Seales but he needs to get a bit closer to the off pole. Nurul Hasan once again plays inside the line of the ball.
WIDE! Jayden Seales has sprayed this one way beyond the tramline outside off and the ball moves away as well. A wide is called.
Better from Seales. This is a bit closer to the off pole, good length and shaping away. Nurul Hasan plays and misses.
Full and around off, moving away from the right-hander, Nurul lets it through to the keeper.
Full again and around the fifth stump line, keeps on shaping it away. Nurul Hasan plays inside the line of the ball.
On a good length, angling it into the off stump. Ebadot Hossain makes a solid block off the front foot.
This is a bit fuller in length and wide of the off stump. Ebadot Hossain watches as the ball goes through to the keeper.
Full and wide, shaping away. No need to play at that one.
And again! Full and wide outside off, Ebadot Hossain doesn't play at it.
Full again but angling down leg this time. Good take from Joshua Da Silva down to his left.
Another maiden over for Kemar Roach but he hardly troubled the batter. Full again, outside off and shaping away. Ebadot Hossain plays inside the line of the ball.
Wonderful shape away first-up from Alzarri Joseph. On a good length outside off, goes through to the keeper.
Brings the line closer on a good length, Nurul Hasan is beaten this time as he hangs his bat down.
Full outswinger just outside off, Nurul Hasan knocks it to short mid on.
Back-of-a-length delivery on off stump. Nurul Hasan gets on his back foot and punches it to covers.

FOUR! Nurul Hasan comes up with his own helicopter shot! Alzarri Joseph bowls this full and outside off, Nurul Hasan thumps it through covers and his arms swing all the way around his head. Stands and admires his shot.
Full this time on off and middle, Nurul Hasan defends this back to the bowler.
In the air but in the gap as well. This is floated up on the pads, Ebadot Hossain with an uppish defensive prod and the ball goes past the man at mid-wicket for a single.
On a length and attacking the stumps, Nurul Hasan goes back and across to work it on the leg side.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A loose shot from Nurul Hasan and both the set batters have now been sent back to the pavilion. Back of a length from Kemar Roach this time and well outside off. Nurul Hasan goes chasing after a wide one and looks to slap it through the line but the ball takes the outside edge and Joshua Da Silva takes a simple catch behind the sticks. Roach picks up his fourth wicket as Bangladesh lead by 76 runs.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Kemar Roach

Commentary: Dead ball signaled by the umpire! Full and on the pads, Mustafizur Rahman offers no shot but the ball deflects off the pads and races away into the fine leg fence. The runs won't count though.
On a fuller length and angled into leg stump. Mustafizur Rahman keeps it out.
Full again and at the stumps, Mustafizur Rahman backs away and keeps it out on the off side.
On a good length outside off, Ebadot Hossain raises his arms and lets it go.
Alzarri Joseph goes full on off, Ebadot Hossain fends it awkwardly towards point.
Alzarri Joseph goes back to bowling outside off on a good length. Ebadot Hossain leaves this one as well.
Similar delivery slighlty closer to Ebadot Hossain who is unsure whether to play or leave it alone. Goes through to the keeper.
Fuller this time on middle, Ebadot Hossain blocks this back to the bowler.
Full and angling into the pads. Ebadot Hossain gets his bat down in time and knocks it to mid-wicket.

SIX! Mustafizur Rahman chances his arm and gets maximum purchase! A length ball, around the top of off. Mustafizur Rahman just goes hard after it and gets a top edge that flies all the way over the third man fence for a maximum.
Good length, over middle. Mustafizur Rahman backs away looking to cut but is beaten for pace.
Full and wide, Mustafizur Rahman has a go at this one as well but fails to connect.
Very full and outside off, shaping away a touch. Mustafizur Rahman makes room looking to go over cover but misses.
Back of a length, outside off. Mustafizur Rahman is able to guide it past point and collects a single.
Beaten! This is angled in on a length from outside off. The ball straightens after pitching and goes past the outside edge of Ebadot Hossain's willow.

OUT! Cleaned him up! Alzarri Joseph knocks over Mustafizur Rahman and West Indies are now one wicket away from bundling out Bangladesh for the second time in this Test match. Joseph comes from around the wicket and angles it in from around off. The ball goes on with the angle as Mustafizur Rahman tries to swing across the line. Rahman misses and the ball goes on to hit the top of leg stump. Joseph picks up his third wicket and Bangladesh currently lead by 83 runs.
Howout: b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: Full and outside off, Khaled Ahmed just keeps his bat in front of his pads and the ball goes through to the keeper.
Full on middle, Khaled Ahmed blocks this awkwardly.
Alzarri Joseph pulls the length back a bit and bowls an outswinger outside off stump. Khaled Ahmed tries to play at it and gets beaten.
Good-length delivery angled into the pads. Khaled Ahmed somehow manages to fend it down towards short leg.
Alzarri Joseph attempts a yorker but gets it wide from off stump. Khaled Ahmed plays it towards covers.
Starts off with a shortish delivery over middle. Ebadot Hossain gets nicely behind the line and makes the block.
Attempted yorker this time, around off. Ebadot Hossain jams it out towards short cover.
This is banged in short but outside off. Ebadot Hossain plays inside the line of the ball.

Joshua Da Silva is certain that there is bat involved and lets out a strong appeal but the umpire remains unmoved. This is a good bouncer, banged in over middle. Ebadot Hossain tries to awkwardly fend it off but the ball seems to have just gone over his bat. There might have been a glove involved but West Indies have no review remaining.

OUT! KNOCKED HIM OVER! Kemar Roach with a sensational five-wicket haul and he has bundled out the opposition in a hurry here. This is on a length, nipping back in from around off and this one stays low. Ebadot Hossain looks to defend but is undone by the lack of bounce and the ball castles into the middle stump. Roach picks up his 50th wicket at this venue and also goes on level with Michael Holding with 249 Test wickets. Bangladesh have been bundled out for 245!
Howout: b Kemar Roach

Commentary: Off the mark straightaway! Mustafizur Rahman starts off with a fullish delivery on off and shaping it back into the right-hander. Kraigg Brathwaite plays at it with soft hands and nudges it past the point region for a single. West Indies are underway.
This is fuller and outside off, shaping away. John Campbell lets it through to the keeper.
Lovely away shape on the ball but just a bit too wide to make the batter play at it. This is on a length and outside off, zipping through to the keeper.
A touch shorter now, around off. Campbell hangs back and fabs it down towards fourth slip.
Full and well outside off, swinging away. John Campbell just shadow-drives inside the line of the ball.
Mustafizur Rahman angles this one into the left-hander, close to the off stump. John Campbell punches it off the front foot towards cover.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A very good catch from Nurul Hasan down to his left and Khaled Ahmed strikes on the very first ball. Khaled starts off with a length ball that is angled down the leg side, Kraigg Brathwaite tries to tickle it fine but gets a faint edge on it. Nurul is quick to move across to his left and takes a stunning catch. Brathwaite walks back early after a soft dismissal and Bangladesh are all pumped up.
Howout: c Nurul Hasan b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary: Around the top of off, Raymon Reifer stays inside the crease to watchfully keep it out.
Slightly shorter in length, on leg stump. Raymon Reifer tucks it off his hips and towards deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Khaled Ahmed switches to around the wicket and bowls this one wide of the off stump. Raymon Reifer leaves it alone.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A double strike from Khaled Ahmed in his very first over and all of a sudden the game is turned on its head. Real loose this though from Raymon Reifer. Khaled angles it in on a good length and around off. Reifer is caught in two minds but decides to leave it. Reifer is late and the ball bounces a bit extra taking the bottom part of the glove. Nurul Hasan makes no mistake behind the sticks and West Indies are two down inside the first two overs. 81 needed to win now.
Howout: c Nurul Hasan b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary: Full and outside off, swinging away. Nkrumah Bonner shoulders arms at it. Just two runs and a couple of wickets in the over for Khaled Ahmed.
Pitched up, around off. John Campbell drives it stylishly and times it well but finds the fielder at covers.
Length this time, close to the off pole. Campbell defends it out.
FOUR! John Campbell is off the mark with a boundary. A touch full and wide, Campbell goes on the front foot and drives it past point for the first boundary of the innings.
This is angled onto the pads, Campbell works it around the corner towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Slightly back of a length and slanted across the right-hander. Nkrumah Bonner watches it go past him and through to the keeper.

A stifled appeal for lbw but going down leg probably. Pitches it up this time and around leg stump. Nkrumah Bonner falls over a bit as he looks to flick it away. Bonner gets hit on the pads but and the ball rolls onto the leg side. The replay shows that the ball is pitching outside leg stump.
On a good length and outside off. John Campbell looks to play at it but is beaten past the outside edge.

John Campbell looks for two but is sent back by his partner. This is angled in from around off and once again, John Campbell is caught in two minds. Campbell opts to leave it late and the ball goes off the face of the bat towards deep backward point. The batters pick up a single.

A huge appeal for caught behind and the keeper seems certain but it is turned down. On a good length, around off and shaping away. Nkrumah Bonner looks to play at it away from his body but gets beaten past the outside edge. The Bangladesh players all go up in unison but the umpire remains unmoved. Shakib Al Hasan does review it but UltraEdge shows that there's a clear gap between bat and ball. NOT OUT!
On off and angling in, Bonner keeps it out on the leg side.

OUT! Cleaned up! Khaled Ahmed is spitting fire out there and down goes the third wicket for West Indies. This is delivered on a good length and around off. The ball jags back in a long way and stays a bit low as well, skidding through. Nkrumah Bonner is a bit late on the defensive shot and ends up getting beaten for pace. The ball knocks the off stump out of the ground and Khaled is running away in celebration. 75 runs needed now with 7 wickets in hand.
Howout: b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary: Back of a length, around off. Jermaine Blackwood defends it off the back foot. End of yet another successful over from Khaled Ahmed.
Right on the money! Around the top of off, Campbell keeps it out.
Slightly fuller and on off, Campbell pushes it back towards the bowler.
On a nagging length, angled into middle. The ball straightens a bit and John Campbell just about manages to get his bat in front of the pad to make the block.
Nice change up from Mustafizur Rahman as he takes all the pace off the ball and bowls it full and wide. Campbell is beaten all ends up.

Ooh, the ball just took off there! Mustafizur Rahman bends his back and bowls it on a hard length outside off. John Campbell looks to cut it away but the ball shoots up sharply off the surface and goes through to the keeper.
Off-cutter this time from Mustafizur Rahman. On a good length, angling into the body. Campbell looks to defend but misses the ball and gets hit on the body. Maiden!
FOUR! Jermaine Blackwood glances this fine! Khaled Ahmed misses his line and bowls this down leg stump on a good length. Jermaine Blackwood does not miss out as he gets a boundary to fine leg.
Middle stump line on a good length. Jermaine Blackwood knocks it towards mid-wicket. Tamim Iqbal collects it and has a shy at the bowlers end.
Full and on middle. Defended back to the bowler.
Khaled Ahmed bowls full once again, angling into the pads. Jermaine Blackwood works it to square leg.
Full and outside off stump. Jermaine Blackwood lets this one go.
Good-length delivery on middle. Jermaine Blackwood works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller in length and angled across the off stump. Jermaine Blackwood blocks it out.
Pitched up this time, around off. Jermaine Blackwood gets a good stride forward and solidly defends it out.
Slower in pace, angling across the batter. Blackwood punches it out towards mid off.
Full and outside off, going across the right-hander. Blackwood lets it through to the keeper.
This is pitched up on the fourth stump line, Blackwood defends it out off the front foot.
Goes around the wicket for the final delivery and bowls it full and straight. Blackwood clips it to the man at square leg and picks up a single.
Bowls this full angling into the pads, Jermaine Blackwood knocks it towards mid on.
Slightly back of a length on off stump. Jermaine Blackwood gets up and punches it towards cover. A misfield allows Jermaine Blackwood to get across for a single.
Back-of-a-length delivery outside off stump. John Campbell strokes it to mid off.

Full and swinging into the pads. John Campbell tries to flick it and falls all over it. Thumps into the pad and Bangladesh players appeal. The umpire reckons its going down leg stump Shakib Al Hasan does not review. The batters cross for a leg bye as well.
Pulls his length back once again on off stump. Jermaine Blackwood gets on top of it and punches it to mid off.
Good-length delivery on off stump, attacking the pads. Jermaine Blackwood defends to down the pitch.
Starts off with a fullish delivery on the pads, John Campbell tickles it around the corner and picks up a couple of runs.
Good running. Flatter and angled into middle. John Campbell backs away and works it into the vacant area around wide mid on. They do come back for the second with ease.
Around the pads, flicked away towards square leg for an easy single.
Nicely floated up, around off. Blackwood defends it out towards cover-point.
On a shorter length and around middle. Blackwood works it off the back foot and in front of mid-wicket for a single.

FOUR! Up and over! This is flighted outside off, John Campbell deliberately goes aerial and lofts it over wide mid off. The fielder from the cover fence tries his best and puts in the dive but can't stop the boundary.  An expensive first over from Mehidy Hasan, 10 runs coming off it.
Good-length delivery on middle. Defended towards mid off.
Khaled Ahmed bowls this short outside off, Jermaine Blackwood tries to cut it but the ball stays low and he mistimes it back to the bowler.
Good-length delivery on middle, Jermaine Blackwood works it wide of mid on for a single.
Full this time outside off, John Campbell leaves it alone.

FOUR! West Indies are getting a move on now! Half volley outside off stump. John Campbell gets forward confidently, strokes it with the open face of his bat towards point for a boundary! 52 more runs needed!
Full once again outside off. John Campbell plays it towards mid off.
Tossed up delivery, on off. Blackwood pushes it towards mid on.
A bit of grip and extra bounce this time. On a length, around off. this one turns in a bit as Blackwood gets an inside edge back onto the pads.
On middle, this is turned towards mid-wicket.
Around off, pushed away tentatively towards cover.
Nicely flighted, drifting into middle. Blackwood works it towards wide mid on.
On middle and leg, flicked away leg side. End of a maiden over from Mehidy Hasan.

FOUR! Smashed! Ebadot Hossain bowls a loose delivery to start off. It is short and wide and gives John Campbell all the time in the world to give himself room and hammer it between cover and long off for a boundary! 48 more runs needed now.
Goes around the wicket, but still bowls it short and wide of off stump, John Campbell does not connect and will feel he missed out on this one.
Goes slightly fuller outside off stump. John Campbell tries to cut it but the ball stays low and beats him.
Short outside off once again, Works it towards the cover fielder.
Back-of-a-length delivery outside off, John beats the cover fielder this time and gets a single.

FOUR Thick outside edge and runs to the boundary! Ebadot Hossain bowls it short, and gets extra bounce outside off stump. Takes Jermaine Blackwood by surprise as it takes a thick edge and runs past third slip for a boundary!
Slightly short and on off, John Campbell goes on the back foot and defends it down.
Shortish again, around off, John again plays it down from the back foot.
Closer to off, continues to be short, Campbell stays back to defend.
Drags his length short around off, John pulls it unconvincingly to mid on for a run.
Flighted arm ball around off, Jermaine Blackwood defends it in front of his front pad.
Loopy and full, around off, Blackwood presses forward and blocks it safely. West Indies are halfway there, 42 more needed.
Short in length and wide outside off, Campbell tries to cut but misses.
On a length and around off, John taps it down to covers and steals a single.
Back of a length, around off, Jermaine Blackwood defends it down from the back foot.
Digs it in short, around middle and leg, Jermaine jumps and tucks it in front of square leg for an easy two.
Aims for a yorker but it turns out to be a low full toss, around off, Jermaine drives it through cover-point for a run.
Fullish and around off, it's speared in, Campbell gets forward and defends it off the inner half to mid-wicket. The ball rolls in the gap and they cross. 37 needed more.
Full and flighted on off, Campbell knocks it down to long on for a run.
Loopy and around off, Jermaine is forward as he blocks it to the leg side.
Slightly short in length, just outside off, Blackwood goes on the back foot and whacks it to deep cover for a single.
Arm ball, landing around leg and skidding on, Campbell defends it unconvincingly from the back foot.
Fuller and around off, driven to mid off.
Slower through the air, full and around off, John Campbell defends it cautiously off the front foot. That will be Stumps on Day 3.
Fuller in length, around leg, it's clipped behind square leg for a couple.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
On a length and outside off, easy leave for the batter again.
Around off, a bit full in length, Blackwood is forward as he defends.
A bit of movement, from a length around off, Jermaine taps it down to point and takes a run.
Lands it full and on off, John defends it off the front foot to point. They cross for a run.
Ebadot runs in from 'round the wicket and angles in a length ball on off, Campbell defends it from the front foot.
Play and a miss! Short in length and outside off, Campbell tries to cut but it bounces over his blade.
FOUR! First of the boundary. Angling down the leg side, on a length, Campbell clips it off his pads and it scoots away to the fine leg fence. 27 needed more.
FOUR! Bang! The 50-run stand comes up. Short in length and wide outside off, John Campbell stands tall inside the crease and slaps it through point for another boundary. 23 more needed.
Slants it in, on a good length around off, Campbell goes on the back foot and defends it down on the pitch.
A hint of inward movement there, from a length around off, Campbell closes the face of his bat and nudges it through backward square leg. Calls for two and gets two. 10 from the over!
Lands it on a length, outside off, it's defended back.
Helps a full ball off his pads to backward square leg for a run.
The batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Short and wide, cut from the back foot but straight to the point fielder.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller and outside off, pushed back off the front foot.
This time there is some extra bounce as it lands on a good length and holds its line outside off. Jermaine Blackwood goes fishing for it and gets beaten.
Serves it on a length and outside off, Jermaine Blackwood takes a positive stride forward and drives it through covers for three runs.
Back of a length, on off, John is on the back foot in defense.
Back of a length, wide outside off, Campbell stays back and cuts it through backward point for a single.
Fraction short, around off and shaping back in, Blackwood stays back and glances it behind square leg for a couple.
On a length and outside off, angling in, Campbell presses forward and gently pushes it to the off side.
Delivers it on a length and outside off, a hint of inward shape there, Campbell plays inside the line and lets it through to the keeper.
Serves it on a length again, outside off and shaping back in, John covers his stumps and shoulders arms.

FOUR! Extra bounce this time, on a length and outside off, Campbell plays at it with an angled bat and guides it with soft hands. Deliberately keeps it down and places it wide of the slip cordon. The ball races away to the third man fence. 10 more to win.
In the channel outside off, on a length and going almost straight on with extra bounce, Campbell attempts the punch but away from the line of the delivery.
FOUR! Excellent shot! Campbell moves to 48 with this boundary. Fuller in length and outside off, John presses forward and strokes it elegantly through covers.
Starts by delivering it very full, around off and drifting in, Blackwood pushes it down to mid on.
Flatter and a touch shorter, around off, it's defended from the back foot.
Quicker and around off, again it's blocked from the back foot.
Loopy and full, around off, Jermaine is on the front foot in defense.
Mehidy pulls his length back and lands it around off, Jermaine Blackwood goes on the back foot and offers a dead bat.
Extra loop on this delivery. It lands and breaks back in, Jermaine Blackwood lunges to defend and keeps it out off the inner half to square leg.
Drifting down the leg side, John moves back and helps it to square leg.
FOUR! Full and flighted, around middle, Campbell gets down on one knee and sweeps it to fine leg for a boundary. FIFTY FOR CAMPBELL! Two needed more.
Short in length and outside off, John cracks it off his back foot but finds the cover fielder.
Fuller and around off, defended off the front foot.
Short and outside off, Campbell goes hard at it and mistimes his square-cut to covers.
SIX! Campbell finishes it off in style! Tossed up around off, fuller in length, John Campbell latches onto it and smacks it all the way over long off for a biggie. West Indies win by 7 wickets!
